name: Abániwọ́ndá
extended meaning: Like "Àbánikándá", this name boasts that the enemies can only try, they can't succeed.

name: Abégúnrìn
meaning: One who is born during egúngún festival, or who walks with egúngún.

name: Abéjidé
meaning: One who comes with the rain.

name: Abéjirìn
meaning: One who was birth when it's raining.
extended meaning: A child born during a rainstorm. See also: Abéjidé.

name: Abérìṣàdé
extended meaning: Many of the names listed under this "Foreign-General" tag were found in old printed sources, and may have been spelt wrongly or according to the orthographic limitations of the times. For this reason, they may not always correspond to modern spellings. They are included in this dictionary as a way to guide those who found them and came here to look for their meaning to the right meaning and the right contemporary spellings of the names. These sources are from old Lagos publications, likely influenced by foreign returnees from Cuba and Brazil.

name: Abésùjobì
meaning: One who eats kola nuts with Èṣù

name: Abéṣùpínlẹ̀
meaning: One brave enough to share a piece of land with Èṣù.

name: Abégúndé
meaning: The one who came with the masquerade.

name: Abìjà
extended meaning: The full appellation is "abìjàwàrà bí ẹkùn", meaning one with a fighting spirit as fierce as the tiger's.

name: Abídákun
meaning: The lastborn. Literally: one born to end all future births.

name: Abídè
extended meaning: Like Abídèmí, this is a name given to a child born before the father's return from a long trip.

name: Abídogun
meaning: Given birth to in anticipation of war.

name: Abídoyè
meaning: Born before title/rank. Born in the anticipation of gaining a title/rank.

name: Abílàwọ́n
meaning: One given birth to in the middle of the rest.
extended meaning: Like Ọ̀kánlàwọ́n, this name is given to a child of a different gender born after a streak of having children of the same gender. For instance, the first female child born after five male children were born will be Ọ̀kánlàwọ́n or Abílàwọ́n: born to diffuse the gender streak.

name: Abíléọlá
meaning: HOMOGRAPH 1. One given birth to after tremendous wealth (Abíléọlá. Also Àbíléọlá) 2. One given birth to in the home of wealth (Abíléọlá. e.g. A bí ní ilé ọlá)

name: Abíminá
meaning: We have given birth to me already.

name: Abímisíreolúwa
meaning: I have been born into the goodness of God.

name: Abímpé
extended meaning: It could be translated to mean a perfectly healthy child, that is, birthed without any blemish or disabilities.

name: Abínúwáíyé
meaning: One who came into the world angry.

name: Abínúwáyé
meaning: One who comes into the world angry.

name: Abísáyọ̀
meaning: Born into happiness or into joy.

name: Abíshọlá
extended meaning: Not to be confused with Abísọ́lá.

name: Abíọ́jà
meaning: One given birth to in the marketplace.

name: Abíọ́kọ̀
meaning: One that was given birth to in a vehicle.

name: Abíádé
extended meaning: It's a name associated with royal children.

name: Abídèmí
meaning: The child born before I returned.
extended meaning: It's a name typically given to a child born when the father was away out of town/country.

name: Abíkóyè
meaning: Given birth to in addition to the chieftaincy.
extended meaning: It's most likely given to a child born after the parent has earned a notable chieftaincy role (or kingship)

name: Abímbádé
meaning: I was born with the crown.
extended meaning: The "adé" (crown) component of the name shows it to be a name given to a child from a royal family.

name: Abímbólú
meaning: I was born into a family of champions.

name: Abímbóyè
meaning: I was born with the chieftaincy.

name: Abíóyè
extended meaning: in Ọ̀yọ́, this will usually be a name for a child (male or female) born to a sitting Aláàfin. In other Yoruba towns, a chuld born maybe after a chieftaincy has been conferred on a parent gets this name. Generally reserved for royal families

name: Abírí
meaning: We've given birth to him/her before.

name: Abíọ́nà
meaning: 1. Born into the arts. 2. Born on the way.
extended meaning: The name Abíọ́nà (given birth to on the road) is usually given to a child either literally born on the road, or someone born during a notable transition period in the lives of the parents.

name: Abíọ́sẹ̀
extended meaning: A child born on a day traditionally set aside for the worship of Ifá, or any of the orisas.

name: Abógunrìn
meaning: One who was born at wartime.

name: Abólúdé
meaning: One who came with the lord.

name: Abóndé
meaning: The one who came with a significant occasion.

name: Abórìshàdé
meaning: One who returns with the Òrìṣà.

name: Abórìṣàdé
meaning: One who came with the òrìṣà.

name: Abóyèjí
meaning: 1. One who wakes up with chieftaincy/honour. 2. We woke up with chieftaincy/honour.

name: Abulẹ̀ṣowó
meaning: One who makes wealth from tilling the soil.

name: Aburúmákú
meaning: The one who is wicked yet won't die.

name: Abùlátàn
meaning: (One with) plenty of roasted meat to pick from. A great hunter. [See extra information below.]
extended meaning: Atàn is where meat is roasted. Abùlátàn is the name for someone reputed to have so much meat on the roast. .e.g. a great hunter.

name: Abáfárìn
meaning: One who travels/walks with the (ifá) priesthood/corpus

name: Abíbádé
meaning: Born with/into royalty. The birth of the child found royalty in the family.

name: Abídúró
meaning: A child that was birth to live.

name: Abímbésú
meaning: I was born in the year of the locusts.

name: Abímifólúwa
meaning: I was born for the lord

name: Abíára
extended meaning: A name given to a child suspected to be a product of inbreeding/incest. [citation/verification needed]

name: Abólúwají
meaning: One who wakes with the God.

name: Abólúwapé
meaning: A child who's completed with the Lord.

name: Abẹ̀rùàgbà
extended meaning: A nickname. Abẹ̀rùàgbà is the opening phrase in the proverbial sentence: Abẹ̀rùàgbà ni yó tẹlẹ̀ yí pẹ́ (only the respectful will live long).

name: Abẹ́lẹ́shindọ́gba
meaning: One who is as prominent as the horseman.

name: Abẹ́lẹ́ṣindọ́gba
meaning: One who is as prominent as the horseman.

name: Abọ́badé
meaning: He who comes with the king.

name: Abọ́barìn
meaning: He who walks/fellowships with the king.

name: Abọ́dúndé
extended meaning: Children born during the native festive seasons, including modern ones like Christmas, Easter, Eid-el-Fitr, etc are given this name.

name: Abọ́dúnrìnká
meaning: One who walks around with festivities.

name: Abọ́dúnrìnwá
meaning: One who arrives with the year. One who arrives with the season. One who arrives with festivities. We arrived with the year. We arrived with the season. We arrived with festivities.

name: Abọ́dúnr̀in
meaning: One who walks with the year.

name: Abọ́lárìn
meaning: One who who walks with wealth.
extended meaning: It is the short form of Abọ́lárìnwá.

name: Abọ́lárìnwá
meaning: One who walks in with wealth.

name: Abọ́láwarìn
meaning: One who walks in with our wealth/success.

name: Abọ́rọ̀dé
meaning: The child came at the same time as success (in the family).

name: Abọ́sẹ̀dá
extended meaning: Many of the names listed under this "Foreign-General" tag were found in old printed sources, and may have been spelt wrongly or according to the orthographic limitations of the times. For this reason, they may not always correspond to modern spellings. They are included in this dictionary as a way to guide those who found them and came here to look for their meaning to the right meaning and the right contemporary spellings of the names. These sources are from old Lagos publications, likely influenced by foreign returnees from Cuba and Brazil.

name: Abọ́sẹ̀dé
meaning: One born with a new week.
extended meaning: This is a name typically given to a child born on Sunday.

name: Abọ́yadé
meaning: One who arrives with the goddess Ọya.

name: Abọ́dẹrìn
meaning: He who walks with the hunters.
extended meaning: Abọ́dẹrìn is a family name of a famous and old family from Kúdẹtì, Ìbàdàn

name: Abọ́lájí
meaning: One who woke up with wealth.

name: Adagbádá
meaning: One who goes around with yards of Agbádá. A wealthy person.
extended meaning: Another way of looking at the name is through the special place that the agbádá garment holds in Yorùbá social life. It signifies wealth and excess such that anyone called by this name is being implied to be very rich.

name: Adàránboríìyàwó
meaning: One who covers their wife's head with velvet.

name: Adálémọ
meaning: One who build by himself without external assistance.

name: Adáralẹ́gbẹ́
meaning: One who is beautiful among company.

name: Adáramódù
meaning: One who is beautiful enough to pick the Odù.

name: Adáramọ́lá
meaning: One who is beautiful with wealth.

name: Adágúnodò
extended meaning:
It is one of the name of ruling houses in Ìwó, Ọṣun State. 

There is a deeper meaning to this name not evident from its surface interpretation. Babalọlá & Àlàbá (2003)'s "A Dictionary of Yorùbá Personal Names" gives the meaning of the name simply as "a lake", calling it a common Yorùbá nickname.

name: Adámọlẹ́kun
meaning: One who makes a child stop crying.

name: Adechiná
extended meaning: A Lukumi name for "Adéshínà", from Brazil.

name: Adegùntẹ́
meaning: The crown has ascended the throne.

name: Adejaju
extended meaning: Many of the names listed under this "Foreign-General" tag were found in old printed sources, and may have been spelt wrongly or according to the orthographic limitations of the times. For this reason, they may not always correspond to modern spellings. They are included in this dictionary as a way to guide those who found them and came here to look for their meaning to the right meaning and the right contemporary spellings of the names. extended meaning: Many of the names listed under this "Foreign-General" tag were found in old printed sources, and may have been spelt wrongly or according to the orthographic limitations of the times. For this reason, they may not always correspond to modern spellings. They are included in this dictionary as a way to guide those who found them and came here to look for their meaning to the right meaning and the right contemporary spellings of the names. These sources are from old Lagos publications, likely influenced by foreign returnees from Cuba and Brazil.

name: Adébàjò
meaning: The crown returns from a trip.

name: Adébàmerun
meaning: The crown of my lineage isn't lost.

name: Adébágbo
meaning: 1. The crown meets the crowd. 2. We arrived to meet the crowd.

name: Adébárá
meaning: 1. The crown meets family. 2. We arrived to meet family.

name: Adébisọ́lá
meaning: The crown gave birth to (this) in nobility/wealth.

name: Adébímpé
meaning: The crown gave birth to me complete.

name: Adébógun
meaning: One who returns to meet war.

name: Adébóyèjọ
meaning: 1. The crown is at one with honour. 2. We arrived to be at one with honour.

name: Adébùsáyọ̀mi
meaning: The crown has added to my joy.

name: Adébúlújọ
meaning: The crown is at one with the town.

name: Adébúmitì
meaning: The crown is incapable of insulting me.

name: Adébọ̀sáyọ̀
meaning: The crown has returned to joy.

name: Adébọ̀sọ́lá
meaning: 1. The crown return into wealth. 2. We returned into wealth.

name: Adébọ̀wálé
extended meaning: "My middle name "Adébọ̀wálé" was chosen to commemorate the crowning of the new Àyàngbúrẹ̀n of Ìkòròdú in the year that I was born. The chosen Ọba Salaudeen Oyèfùsì (Ògúntádé II) was from my family and remained King for 44yrs until his death in 2014 aged 83yrs" - User commentary

name: Adébọ̀ọ́lá
meaning: 1. We returned into wealth. 2. The crown enters into wealth.

name: Adébọ́lájọ
meaning: Royalty is at one with nobility.

name: Adébọ́rọ̀
meaning: 1. The crown meets wealth. 2. We arrived to meets wealth.

name: Adédara
meaning: 1. The crown is good. (Adédára) 2. The crown makes wonders (Adédárà)

name: Adédiba
extended meaning: Many of the names listed under this "Foreign-General" tag were found in old printed sources, and may have been spelt wrongly or according to the orthographic limitations of the times. For this reason, they may not always correspond to modern spellings. They are included in this dictionary as a way to guide those who found them and came here to look for their meaning to the right meaning and the right contemporary spellings of the names. These sources are from old Lagos publications, likely influenced by foreign returnees from Cuba and Brazil.

name: Adédigba
meaning: Royalty/prestige has becomes multiplied into many folds (two hundred).

name: Adédiní
extended meaning: This is a royal name, typically given to the first royal child (usually son).

name: Adédinṣewò
meaning: The crown gives me a chance to try.

name: Adédire
meaning: Good fortune has followed coronation. We were royal, and now we have good fortune.

name: Adédòkun
meaning: The crown becomes the ocean. [verification needed]
extended meaning: A more accurate interpretation will be that the child (born into a royal family) is a harbinger of wealth for the family into which he/she was born.

name: Adédoṣù
meaning: The crown has come of age.

name: Adédùnmóyè
meaning: The crown is sweet with honour.

name: Adédùnní
meaning: The crown is sweet to have. Royalty is worth having.

name: Adédùńbí
meaning: Royalty is good to birth (as one's child).

name: Adédúró
extended meaning: The name might be an àbíkú name given to a child born into a royal family.

name: Adédọjà
extended meaning: "When you create something useful, you will be proud of it and want to show it off or earn money from it, which might lead to you putting it for sale in the market (therefore, that thing is of value to you). That's the link between market and value in the name Adédọjà. It means my royal creation/child (Adé) is so valuable to me that I will show it off to the public/in the market."

name: Adéèjímitẹ́
meaning: Royalty/The Crown will not let me be put to shame.
extended meaning: It is a condensed derivative from the statement, "Adé kò ní jẹ́ kí èmi ó tẹ́"

name: Adéẹ̀kọ́
meaning: 1. The king of knowledge. 2. The crown isn't his.

name: Adéfàjò
meaning: 1. The crown has caused an increase. 2. One that arrives and brings blessings/increase.

name: Adéfikáyọ̀
meaning: The crown has added to joy.

name: Adéfolúrẹ̀
meaning: The crown consoles itself with the lord.

name: Adéfoyèkẹ́mi
meaning: The crown pampered me with a title.

name: Adéfóyèkẹ́
meaning: The crown gives (this one) to honour for cherishing.

name: Adéfúnmbí
meaning: The prince/king has given me this child to birth.

name: Adéfẹwàshọlá
meaning: 1. One who makes success/nobility/wealth with beauty on their arrival. 2. The crown makes success/nobility/wealth with beauty.

name: Adéfẹwàṣọlá
meaning: 1. One who makes success/nobility/wealth with beauty on their arrival. 2. The crown makes success/nobility/wealth with beauty.

name: Adéfọlájù
meaning: The crown is greater because of wealth.

name: Adégbayọ̀
meaning: The crown receives job. We have arrived to receive joy.

name: Adégbémbọ̀
extended meaning: "A crown that brings you back presumably to a place of glory."

name: Adégbénlé
meaning: The crown places me on top.

name: Adégbénró
meaning: Royalty promotes me. The crown uplifts me. Royalty is my pillar.

name: Adégbìlẹrọ̀
meaning: The crown landed to become soft-hearted. [verification needed]

name: Adégboríoyè
meaning: Royalty receives the primacy of honour.

name: Adégboyè
meaning: 1. The crown receives honour. 2. We arrived to receive honour.

name: Adégbuyì
meaning: 1. The crown receives honour. 2. One who arrives to receive honour.

name: Adégbùlúgbé
meaning: The crown hasn't forgotten the town.

name: Adégbọrọ̀
meaning: 1. The crown receives riches. 2. We arrived to receive riches.

name: Adégbọ́bajó
meaning: The crown makes the king dance.

name: Adégùnlóyè
meaning: The crown has had a long reign.

name: Adégẹyè
meaning: The crown befits the title. [verification needed]

name: Adéire
meaning: A crown of goodness. A crown of blessing. A good crown.

name: Adéìkẹ́
meaning: One who has (or whose birth has) crowned the care you enjoy.

name: Adéjuyìgbé
meaning: Royalty has prevented honour from being wasted/destroyed.

name: Adéjùbẹ
meaning: The crown is bigger than that.

name: Adéjùgbàgbé
extended meaning: 'Adé' here can also mean one's ancestral father (especially from a family of royalty). It also sounds as if someone is trying to say 'don't forget the regality of where you come from.'

name: Adéjùyítán
meaning: The crown is more than this.

name: Adéjọjú
meaning: Royalty is precious. The crown is precious.

name: Adékàḿbí
meaning: I was given birth to deliberately by royalty.

name: Adékànmbí
meaning: 1. Royalty chose me to give birth to. 2. It's my turn to birth the crown.
extended meaning: A unique child born into a royal family, as seen in the movie Ó Le Kú by Tunde Kelani.

name: Adékúnbi
meaning: The crown has been added to the family.

name: Adékúoróyè
meaning: The crown is commended for his/her suffering to attain the honour.

name: Adékẹ́yè
extended meaning: The name is also found in use amongst Òndó, Ìgbómìnà, and Offa people. A variant is Adégẹyè, as used by the juju maestro, King Sunny Ade, an Ondo man.

name: Adélaní
meaning: The crown is what we have.

name: Adélàlú
meaning: The crown is widely respected in the town.

name: Adéláyọ̀
meaning: ==Homograph== 1. The crown has joy (Adéláyọ̀) 2. The crown is joy. (Adélayọ̀)

name: Adélókun
meaning: The crown comes with power. The king/prince is strong. Royalty is a strong bond. The crown is resilient.

name: Adélù
extended meaning:
It was the name of one Aláàfin of Ọ̀yọ́.
[Verification needed for the full meaning of the name]

name: Adélọ́dún
meaning: 1. The crown has festivity. 2. One who arrived during a festive time.

name: Adémákindé
meaning: The crown brings valor. Royalty brought the brave one.

name: Adémidoyin
meaning: My crown/heritage has turned to sweetness.

name: Adémigbùjì
meaning: My crown withstands the wind. [verification needed]

name: Adémiládé
meaning: We have capped me with a crown. I have been justified. I have triumphed.

name: Adémímọ́
extended meaning: Most likely a made-up Christian name.

name: Adémorótì
meaning: The crown is who I'm standing with.

name: Adémókoyá
meaning: Royalty helps improve (our) culture of farming.

name: Adémókùnọlá
meaning: Royalty holds onto the rope of success.

name: Adémósù
meaning: The crown picks up the camwood (ointment) to rub on this child.

name: Adémóyèjẹ
meaning: The crown has earned its honour.

name: Adémóyèjọ
meaning: The crown brings the title together.

name: Adémákin
meaning: 1. The crown has selected valor (in this child). 2. We have arrived with valor.

name: Adémápá
meaning: One who arrived to choose the apá tree.
extended meaning: The name is given to children believed to be born to join the company of witches and wizards.

name: Adémárá
meaning: One who has arrived to join the family.

name: Adémásúnmi
meaning: One whose arrival does not bore/tire me.

name: Adémátìí
meaning: One who arrives without any possibility of fading.

name: Adénmólú
meaning: Royalty is continuing to be triumphant.

name: Adéolúpọ̀
meaning: The royalty of the lord is prominent.

name: Adéolúwajùwọ́n
meaning: The crown of the lord is greater.

name: Adéolúwakìítẹ́
meaning: The Lord's crown can never be put to shame.

name: Adéolúwalójù
meaning: God's crown is superior/is the greatest.

name: Adéolúwani
meaning: He/She is the crown of the lord.

name: Adéònigbàgbé
meaning: The king (or crown) does not forget.

name: Adépàtẹìlẹ̀kẹ̀
meaning: The crown spreads a mat of beads.

name: Adépèmísọ́lá
meaning: The crown called me into success.

name: Adépẹ̀rọ̀
extended meaning: "The crown is big enough for you to be calm. The child which is the crown of the parent, requires that the parent puts their mind at rest and leave jàgídí jàgan."

name: Adépọ́nmilé
meaning: The crown has treated me honorably. Royalty treats me with respect.

name: Adéráyè
meaning: The crown has secured a space.

name: Adérìnbọ́lá
meaning: The crown walks to meet wealth.

name: Adérìnlóyè
meaning: 1. The crown walks to receive honour. 2. The crown walks into honour.

name: Adérìnlọ́lá
meaning: The crown walks to have wealth/success.
extended meaning: See also: Adérìnọ́la, Adérìnkọlá, Adérìnbọ́lá and Adérìnsọ́lá

name: Adéríìkẹ́
meaning: The crown sees this fit to pamper.

name: Adérírí
meaning: Whom the crown has seen before.

name: Adéríyè
meaning: 1. Royalty finds value. 2. We arrived to meet life.

name: Adérónmú
meaning: The crown has found someone to choose.
extended meaning: "From a royal lineage.  The name was given to me by my grandfather. He was away in hiding from his brothers. When the ifa choose him to be the Chief. I was born a few months after his ìwúyè."

name: Adéróunmú
meaning: Royalty chooses well. The king/prince acquires the target. The king/prince finds a thing to acquire. Royalty gets something to possess.

name: Adéróunmúbọ̀
meaning: Royalty found something to bring back.

name: Adérójú
extended meaning: Though expression "rójú" can be interpreted literally to mean "find the eyes", it actually means finding peace. i.e. being clear-eyed enough to observe what is important.

name: Adérẹwà
meaning: The crown is beautiful. Royalty is beautiful.

name: Adérọ̀gbàyímiká
meaning: Royalty builds a protective fence around me.

name: Adérọ́láyọ̀
meaning: 1. Royalty found wealth (in this child) and rejoices. 2. I have come to see wealth and rejoice.

name: Adésanmókùn
meaning: Royalty is improved by its relationship to nobility.

name: Adésátìn
meaning: Unknown. Maybe Adésátì: A crown worth hiding behind.
extended meaning: Many of the names listed under this "Foreign-General" tag were found in old printed sources, and may have been spelt wrongly or according to the orthographic limitations of the times. For this reason, they may not always correspond to modern spellings. They are included in this dictionary as a way to guide those who found them and came here to look for their meaning to the right meaning and the right contemporary spellings of the names. These sources are from old Lagos publications, likely influenced by foreign returnees from Cuba and Brazil.

name: Adésèlúká
meaning: Royalty is famous all around town.

name: Adéshínà
extended meaning: A name given to a child born after a long period of barrenness.

name: Adésíre
meaning: 1. One who arrives into goodness. 2. We arrive into goodness.

name: Adésóyè
meaning: 1. One who arrives into wealth. 2. We arrive into wealth.

name: Adésọpé
meaning: The crown has issued a decree. The crown has spoken wisely.

name: Adésọ̀ràntì
meaning: The crown did not fail to resolve a conflict

name: Adétáyọ̀
meaning: Royalty satisfies a festive spirit. Royalty is as good as happiness. Being royalty is good enough to make one joyful.

name: Adétimọlé
meaning: The crown has found its home.

name: Adétonimí
meaning: 1. It's about time the crown owns me. 2. The crown is capable of owning me.

name: Adétómikẹ́
meaning: The crown is enough for me to cherish.

name: Adétóní
meaning: It is good to be royalty. The crown is worth having.

name: Adétóóyangàn
meaning: The crown is worth boasting with.

name: Adétórera
meaning: The crown is enough for loving oneself. [verification needed]

name: Adétugbọ́gbọ̀

extended meaning:
User feedback:

Adébulé, an Ìjẹ̀bú name, was given to a prince born a few weeks after his father, Mámowórá the son of Adéfalà the crown prince, had died in his house which got burnt after an explosion possibly while celebrating the recent victory and return from the Eluku war also called Matiluko war. The literary translation and meaning of the name was Adé "the crown" - éè bá "that did not meet" -  Ilé "the royal residence or house". 

Adébulé Àgbọ́ngbáorí was himself a territorial guard and warrior who led the Ìjẹ̀bú warriors against the might of the British. Expeditionary forces in May 1892 at the famous Ìmàgbọn or Adáná Sungbọ́ war. 

The various corruptions of the name includes Adébulémọ́, Adébuléjọ, Adébuléwá, Adébulẹ́hìn, Adégbulé, through which from his days as as territorial guard he left a family wherever he served. 

He was born c. 1845, was a younger than his nephew the famous Balógun Odueuungbo Kúkù. He died on the 19th of September in Ìjẹ̀bú Òde and was buried at Ọ̀fin in Ṣàgámù being a direct descendant of Àkárìgbò Liyangu, his great great grandfather, Akárìgbò Tọwọ́bagbé, his grandfather, and the crown prince Mámówórá was his father. Àgbọ́ngbáorí mother was from Iyanro, and he married a princess called Adéjọńwò of the Gbélégbùwà Royal family from Iyanro in Ìjẹ̀bú Òde.

name: Adéwùsì
extended meaning:
The name Adéwùsì, sometimes, spelt and pronounced 'Adéùsì, is the Family name of a royal stock in Ijebu-Ode in Ogun State, Nigeria. The prefix - 'Ade' - (Crown) confirms that bearers of the name are of royal birth. Adewusi or Adeusi Family in Ijebu-Ode is one of the branches of the larger Gbelegbuwa Ruling House, one of the ruling houses in Ijebu-Ode which produce Awujale - the paramount traditional ruler of Ijebuland in Ogun State. Gbelegbuwa Family ' the royalty that earned glory by his character from home or his source') produced the immediate past Awujale of Ijebuland- Oba Daniel Adesanya. The homestead of the Adewusi Family is Odo-Esa in Iwade Quarters of Ijebu-Ode. Odo-esa hosts the shrine of a diety known as Obinrin-Ojowu (the jealous woman). Ogboroganda whose appellation is Obanta ( the King is outside') was reputed to have on his arrival at Odo-Esa in Ijebu-Ode from Ile-Ife, planted or stuck his mystic staff in the ground which staff grew into a mighty boabao tree and diety which Ijebus appease with dogs. Oral history held that Ogboranganda was a grandson of Olu-Iwa, the progenitor of all Ijebus who led the first wave of migration from Ile-Ife to found Ijebuland... 

See: Ògúnwùsì

meaning: Among cuban practitioners of Yoruba spiritual tradition, the belief is that the name means "the crown of the dead." In Yorùbá language of west Africa, the name "Adégún" means "the crown is symmetrical/in good order." Names with the word "adé" (crown) may, at times, be given to those born into royal lineages.
extended meaning: This Cuban version of the Yorùbá name is used as a name for an Òrìṣà initiate and is believed by Cuban practitioners to make reference to the dead (ancestors).

name: Akínṣemóyin
extended meaning:
User comment:
"May this might help with meaning: The news of a minor in line for succession was conveyed back to Benin. The order was summarily issued appointing Gabaro’s uncle, Akinsemoyin, to the throne until the infant heir was old enough for the throne. Thus, Akinsemoyin was crowned the fourth Eleko of Eko. Incidentally but significantly, there is a difference in meaning between the two versions of Akinsemoyin’s name. In the Benin version, Akinshinmoye or Akinseymoyin of this name meant that the older people of the family, being strong and wise even when he was young, should hold office. The Yoruba meaning is Ki Akin se fi owo mu oye na, bravery gladdens me."

name: Ala Iña
meaning: Among practitioners of Cuban Òrìṣà tradition, the Yorùbá-based religious tradition that developed in the island of Cuba, the name Ala Iña is said by practitioners to mean "the mantle of fire (from the core of the earth)." It is a name given to initiates of Santería/Lucumí. The name is derived from the Yorùbá name "O̩láníyan," which, in Yorùbá language, means "wealth/nobility has a proud gait/swagger." In Yorùbá culture it is given to a newborn as a result of a birth within nobility.
extended meaning: This name is used for some initiates within Cuban Òrìṣà tradition, known alternately as Santería, Lucumí, or Regla de Ocha.

extended meaning: Full name: Aníreolúwa (we have the blessing/goodness of God).

name: Ańjọláolúwa
meaning: We're enjoying the wealth of the lord.

name: Ańjọrìn
extended meaning: A longer Yorùbá saying goes "Ańjọrìn, a ò morí olówó" (We walk together, but we don't know who is a future success."

name: Ańwájoyè
meaning: We're on the way to be honoured with royalty.

name: Aofolaju
meaning: Ifá priests are more prominent because of their nobility.

name: Aófọlájùwọ́nlọ
meaning: The priesthood is bigger than them by virtue of nobility.

name: Apálówó
extended meaning: This name appears to reinforce a common Yorùba belief that wealth comes from the work of one's literal hands.

name: Apálará
meaning: The arms are one's closest kin.
extended meaning:
The name comes from the saying "Apá l'ará, ìgùnpá n'ìyekan", meaning "the arms are one's kin and the shoulders are one's step siblings". It is a saying that comes from a popular Yorùbá poem encouraging hard work and self-sufficiency.

See also: Iyelará, Ọmọlará

name: Aperin
extended meaning: One strong enough to defeat a strong obstacle.

name: Apórógunjó
meaning: The weapon pouch is excited at the sight of war.

name: Apónjolósùn
meaning: One who's more fair skinned than one with camwood on their body.

name: Apẹ́lóko
meaning: One who stays longer at the farm (without losing his/her dignity).

name: Apọ́nbíepo
meaning: One that is fair(skinned) like palm oil.

name: Apọ́nmádẹ̀
meaning: One very ripe (or fair-skinned) yet not very soft.

name: Arábámbí
meaning: Family/kin joined to give birth to this.

name: Arájùlù
meaning: Kin is greater than the town.

name: Arámìdé
meaning: 1. My company, kin, or relative, has come. (Arámìdé) 2. My wonder has come (Àràmídé)

name: Aránmọ̀látẹ̀
meaning: We've sent the child to (sell at) the market.

name: Aráolúwa
meaning: 1. The lord's kin (Aráolúwa) 2. The lord's wonder (Àràolúwa)

name: Arápájà
meaning: One with arms competent to fight.

name: Arápáregángan
meaning: One with arms competent enough to dance to the gángan drums.
extended meaning: This is a nick name. It is also the name of a character in a film "Ṣaworoidẹ" (2009) by Mainframe Òpómúléró.

name: Arìnlóye
meaning: One who walks to receive honour.

name: Aríbalóyè
meaning: One with a father in a high position.

name: Aríbidó
meaning: 1. We've found a place to settle/live. 2. One who has found a place to stay.

name: Aríbigbọlá
meaning: One with enough space to store up success.

name: Aríbirè
meaning: One with somewhere to go. Someone that will go places. Someone that will go far in life.

name: Aríbisìn
meaning: We've found a place to worship/serve.

name: Aríbisọ̀gán
meaning: The one who foresaw evil to built a fortress.

name: Arídẹgbé
meaning: One who has found brass bells to carry.
extended meaning: A name given to the devotee of Ọ̀ṣun.

name: Arífálò
meaning: One that sees Ifá to use.

name: Arífáyọ̀
meaning: One who rejoices at the sight of Ifá.

name: Arígbábowó
meaning: One with calabash big enough to gather money. See: Arígbábuwó

name: Arígbábù
meaning: One with a calabash big enough to scoop (money).

name: Aríkúyẹrí
meaning: One who sees death and averts it.

name: Aríléwọlá
meaning: We have found a house in which to nurture wealth.

name: Aríreolúwa
meaning: We have seen the goodness of God.

name: Aríunfáyọ̀
meaning: We have found something (someone) to be grateful for.

name: Aríwàjoyè
meaning: One who brings a good character to this chieftaincy office.

name: Aríyáyọ̀
meaning: One who rejoices at the sight of his/her mother.
extended meaning:
The name is typically given to a child born into a family of many elderly women (parents, grandparents, etc).

See also: Aríyehún

name: Aríyehún
meaning: One who has seen the mother to rejoice with.
extended meaning:
It is given to a child with many women ancestors still living at the time of his birth.

See also: Aríyáyọ̀

name: Aríọrí
meaning: We have seen you before (We saw your in your previous incarnation)
extended meaning: This is a name given to àbíkú children.

name: Aríbisálà
meaning: One who has found a place to run to in order to survive.

name: Arígbábuwó
meaning: 1. One who has the calabash big enough to gather money. 2. We have a calabash big enough to gather money.

name: Aríyìbí
meaning: We've found this one to give birth to.

name: Aríṣekọ́lá
meaning: He who adds success to great wealth.

name: Arotilé
meaning: The one who stands with his/her home.

name: Aróbíodu
meaning: One that makes a sound like the "odu".
extended meaning:
Another way to look at the name is 'one who cries like the bell', or 'one who sounds the warning bells in his song... not a towncrier, but a social activist using his songs.' 

Source: https://twitter.com/dapogundipe/status/983660048252628992

name: Aróbíẹkẹ́
meaning: One who stands firm like the rafter.

name: Arógbọfà
meaning: One strong enough to wait to receive arrows.

name: Arógundádé
meaning: One who puts on a crown on the sight of war.

name: Arógunmátì
meaning: One who doesn't hesitate at the sight of war.

name: Arójòjoyè
meaning: One who accept honours, even in the rain. [verification needed]

name: Arókodáre
meaning: One who is happy to be on the farm.

name: Arókoyọ̀
meaning: One that rejoices at the sight of farming.

name: Arómáshọdú
meaning: The dye makes the cloth black.

name: Arómirẹ́
meaning: One who is friendly with water.

name: Aróniyọ̀
meaning: We've seen the salt seller. [verification needed]

name: Arónkẹ́
meaning: We have found something to care for.

name: Aróunfáyọ̀
meaning: We have found something (someone) worthy to be thankful for.

name: Aróunkẹ́
meaning: We have found something to care for.

name: Arówogbọlá
meaning: One with enough money to gain nobility.

name: Arówóbùsóyè
meaning: One with (enough) money to add to honour.

name: Arówódáṣà
meaning: One who has money to make culture.

name: Arówójolú
meaning: One with enough money to become prominent.
extended meaning: The more literal interpretation would be "One with enough money to eat mushrooms."

name: Arówómọlé
meaning: 1. One with enough money to know his home. 2. One with enough money to build a house.

name: Arówóná
meaning: One with sufficient money to spend.

name: Arówóramímọ́
meaning: One with money to buy holiness.

name: Arówórà
meaning: One with money enough to buy (stuff).

name: Arówóyẹlé
meaning: One who finds money to befit the home.

name: Arówóṣafẹ́
meaning: One with enough money to make fashion.

name: Arówóṣayé
meaning: One who has money to enjoy life.

name: Arówóṣẹgbẹ́
meaning: He with money enough to court (good) company.

name: Aróyègún
meaning: One who finds honour/chieftaincy in order to stand upright.

name: Aróyèhún
meaning: One who rejoices at the sight of chieftaincy.

name: Aróyèwun
meaning: He who rejoices at the sight of chieftaincy/honour.

name: Arómókùn
meaning: One tied up with a rope.

name: Arómọlárà́n
meaning: One who wraps children in velvet.

name: Arúbàlúsì
meaning: One who pays homage to elderly ones and thus became prosperous.

name: Arúléba
meaning: 1. We've found a house to settle in. 2. One with a place to nestle in.

name: Arógunmáyà
meaning: He who sees the advancement of war but never steps aside.

name: Aróhundálejòdúró
meaning: He who has something to refresh visitors thus making them stay longer.

name: Aróhundíyà
meaning: We've got a great possession as compensation for our suffering.

name: Arówólò
meaning: One who has found money to utilize.

name: Arẹ́gbẹ́shọlá
meaning: One made affluent by the wealth of his peers.

name: Arẹ́gbẹ́ṣọlá
meaning: One who finds wealth in company.

name: Arẹ́sẹ̀jábàtá
meaning: One with feet capable of competently dancing bàtá.
extended meaning: This is a nickname. It is also the name of a character in a popular movie "Ṣaworoidẹ"(1999) by Mainframe Òpómúléró.

name: Arọ̀lóyè
meaning: 1. One with the gentle honour. 2. One relieved of honour.

name: Arọ̀máyé
meaning: One who clings to the world. [verification needed].

name: Arọ́lákẹ́
meaning: We've found a child (as wealth) to cherish.

name: Arọ́láyọ̀
meaning: 1. One who rejoices at the sight of nobility/wealth. 2. We rejoice at the sight of nobility/wealth/success, etc

name: Arọ́lásùnlé
meaning: One who finds wealth/honour to sleep on.

name: Asájú
extended meaning:
Also written as Aṣaájú.
See: Aṣíwájú

name: Ashọ́nibárẹ
meaning: One who carefully selects whom they relate with.

name: Asíndẹmádé
meaning: One who sews brass into the crown.

name: Asọjí
meaning: 1. We have risen. 2. The risen one.

name: Atilọ́lá
meaning: 1. We now have wealth. 2. We have had wealth.

name: Atinúmọ̀
meaning: One that has been known since they were in the womb.

name: Atirọ́lá
meaning: 1. We now have renown/nobility/success. 2. We have now seen wealth/success.

name: Atóyèbí
meaning: One big enough to birth chieftaincy.

name: Atúnramú
meaning: One who goes back to prepare (for war).
extended meaning: This can be seen as an àbíkú name, representing the acknowledgment of the new child as a returned former one, now better fortified for the world.

name: Atínwọ́rẹ
meaning: The gift we have been looking for.

name: Atòórọ̀
meaning: Since dawn. Been here from the beginning. Likely. ashort form of a longer name like Atòórọ̀mọlá.

name: Atóperí
extended meaning: One of the names used to sing praises to God. A cognomen.

name: Atúnraṣe
meaning: One who takes care of his/her appearance.

name: Atẹ̀lóyè
extended meaning: A name given to someone born immediately after the parent was given a title.

name: Atẹ́wọ́gbọlá
meaning: One who spreads their hands for blessings.

name: Atọ́baṣe
meaning: The king's dresser. He/she who dresses the king.

name: Atọ́lágbé
meaning: 1. One big enough to live in wealth. 2. One capable enough to carry wealth/nobility.

name: Atọ́yọ̀sóyè
meaning: One who adds sweetness to honour.

name: Atọ́batẹ́lẹ̀
meaning: One who was worthy of kingship before ascending the throne.

name: Aúdù
meaning: Yorùbá's version of the Arabic name "Abdullah".
extended meaning: The original source of the name is Abdullahi, then it was shortened to Abudu, and later to Audu.

name: Awáyéwáserere
meaning: One who comes into the world to do good.

name: Awóbàjò
meaning: The herbalist returned from the trip.

name: Awóbíyí
meaning: The cult gave birth to this.

name: Awóbọtù
extended meaning: If you know what this name means, please provide it using the "Improve this entry" button above.

name: Awódẹ̀ìn
meaning: The cult is in the past. [verification needed]
extended meaning: It's another way of writing Awódẹ̀yìn.

name: Awófisáyọ̀
meaning: The oracle adds to our joy.

name: Awófẹ̀sọ̀
meaning: The cult uses peace... [an abridged version of a longer name]

name: Awófẹ̀sọ̀bí
meaning: The priesthood gave birth to (this) in peace.

name: Awófọlájù
meaning: The priesthood is prominent by virtue of its nobility.

name: Awójùlù
meaning: The force/being of secret knowledge reveals something new. The unknown forces of nature surprise us.
gloss: [{'awó': ' - mystery, secret, society or body or being of secret knowledge'}]

name: Awójùlúgbé
meaning: The herbalist will not let the town suffer in vain.

name: Awókùlẹ́hìn
meaning: There are members of the cult/priesthood left behind.
gloss: [{'awo': ' - priesthood, cult, members of the cult/priesthood'}]

name: Awókùlẹ́yìn
meaning: There are more members of the cult/priesthood left behind.
gloss: [{'awo': ' - cult, members of a cult, priesthood'}]

name: Awólàlú
meaning: Ifá is widely worshiped (all over town)

name: Awómọ̀lọ̀
meaning: The oracle knows how to grind it. [verification needed]

name: Awóreni
gloss: [{'awo': ' - cult, members of a cult, priesthood'}]

name: Awótóyè
meaning: The Oracle is worth the title.

name: Awótúnsìn
meaning: The oracle is worth worshipping. [verification needed]

name: Awótọ̀nà
meaning: The oracle followed the right path.

name: Awóyẹni
meaning: The priesthood is befitting of one.
gloss: [{'awo': ' - the priesthood, the cult, the oracle, the diviner'}]

name: Awóbokun
meaning: The (child of) Ifá priesthood meets the ocean.

name: Awóbódù
meaning: The priesthood met the ifá corpus.

name: Awójọbí
meaning: The oracle contributed to the birth of this.

name: Awómódù
meaning: The cult/priesthood is at one with the Ifá corpus. [Verification needed]

name: Awósìkà
meaning: The oracle does not do evil.

name: Awóyinfá
gloss: [{'awo': ' - initiated people, ifá diviners, cult members'}]

name: Awóyẹlé
meaning: The oracle belongs in the house.

name: Awóyọkùn
meaning: The oracle has grown a potbelly (has grown wealthy).

name: Awoọlá
meaning: The priesthood of wealth/success. The wealthy priesthood (of Ifá).

name: Awódoyè
meaning: (Being an) initiate has become a position (of honour).

name: Awódìran
extended meaning: See also: Ọládìran, Oyèdìran, Adédìran, Olúdìran...

name: Awófisan
meaning: Ifá used this (child) to pay me (as a replacement for a previous loss)

name: Awópìtàn
meaning: Ifá/Ifá priest told the story/revealed something unknown (with the birth of the child).
gloss: [{'awo': ' - Ifá, the Ifá priesthood, Ifá divination'}]

name: Awórelé
extended meaning: This is a name given to a child born after the death of a prominent member of the family.

name: Awósanmí
meaning: Ifa (worship) is beneficial to me; brought me good things.

name: Awótúndé
meaning: Ifá priest/member of the family is back (from a belief in reincarnation of the spirit of a dead relative)

name: Awóyalé
meaning: The fraternity (e.g. of Ifá) came by the house (reincarnated).

name: Awóṣọpẹ́
meaning: Ifá priest/initiate gives thanks (for the child or the circumstances surrounding the birth).

name: Awọ̀lúmátẹ́
meaning: One who is never disgraced on entering a (new) town/place.

name: Ayànyẹmí
extended meaning: See also: Adéyẹmí, Oyèyẹmí, Olúyẹmí, Ọláyẹmí, etc

name: Ayégbeni
meaning: Earth is favourable to one (to me).

name: Ayéjùsùnlé
meaning: You can't rely on the world.

name: Ayékòótọ́
extended meaning: Also a name given to the parrot in Yorùbá, along with Odídẹrẹ́.

name: Ayékẹ
meaning: One loved, cared for, by all.
extended meaning:
User comment on a homographic equivalent: Ayẹ́kẹ́: 
"I just heard from a reliable source that it's actually Ayẹ́kẹ́ not Ayékẹ. I really have no idea what that means but I remember growing up, we used to call people with bowlegs Ayẹ́kẹ́. I'm assuming that was just his nickname." (Received on February 28, 2017)

name: Ayélabẹ́gàn
meaning: We met scorn as a form of human behaviour.

name: Ayélàágbé
meaning: Earth is the only place where we can live.

name: Ayéle
meaning: Living is hard. The world is difficult.

name: Ayémọ̀la
meaning: 1. The world knows tomorrow. 2. The world doesn't not know tomorrow.

name: Ayéọ̀la
extended meaning: The full proverb: "Ayé Òla kò yé ẹnìkan".

name: Ayélẹ́rù
meaning: The world has frights. The world is a scary place.

name: Ayìnkẹ́
meaning: One meant to praise and pet.

name: Ayántúnjí
extended meaning: A child born shortly after the death of a loved relative in a drummer family.

name: Ayéòríbẹ̀
meaning: The world isn't like that. [verification needed]

name: Ayìnbọ́
extended meaning:
This is a cognomen.

[If anyone is familiar with any other interpretation to the name, please leave it as a comment on "improve this entry" above.]

name: Ayẹni
meaning: He or that which is deserving or befitting.
extended meaning:
User feedbacks:

"My great-great-grandfather happened to be a good herbalist, helping people with ailments. He was so good in his profession that despite being an immigrant, he was conferred the title Ayẹni, by the king. Hence his afterbears have borne this name to this day." 

"The name is borne in about 10 states in Nigeria. 6 SouthWest states, 2 North Central states of Kogi and Kwara, Edo and Delta. There is a reigning monarch in Delta with the name."

name: Ayọ̀bámikalẹ́
meaning: Joy goes with me till the end of my days.

name: Ayọ̀bọ̀bọ́lá
meaning: Joy has come to meet with wealth.

name: Ayọ̀bọ́lá
meaning: We now have joy in addition to the riches we had.

name: Ayọ̀darídé
meaning: Joy is back to its place.

name: Ayọ̀dàmọ́lá
meaning: Joy has been added to honour.

name: Ayọ̀dejì
extended meaning: This is a name given when a joyful event /occurrence coincides with the birth of a child. (Our joy has been doubled)

name: Ayọ̀dimẹ́ta
extended meaning: This is a name usually given to the third child. See also: Ayọ̀diméjì

name: Ayọ̀dipúpọ̀
extended meaning: Another form of the name is Ayomidipupo which means my joy becomes plenty

name: Ayọ̀jésù
meaning: The joy of the Lord. The joy of Jesus.

name: Ayọ̀jésùtómi
meaning: The joy of the lord (Jesus) is enough for me.

name: Ayọ̀kánmí
meaning: It is my turn to celebrate. Joy touched me.

name: Ayọ̀kárí
meaning: Joy big enough to go around.

name: Ayọ̀mísojúmi
meaning: I was able to witness my joy.

name: Ayọ̀mípọ́si
meaning: My happinness has gotten much more.

name: Ayọ̀nìfẹ́olúwa
meaning: Happiness is the will of God.

name: Ayọ̀olúwakìítán
meaning: The joy of the lord knows no end.

name: Ayọ̀olúwanimí
meaning: I am the joy of the Lord.

name: Ayọ̀olúwapẹ́títí
meaning: The joy of the Lord is everlasting/forever.

name: Ayọ̀olúwáṣèyífúnmi
meaning: The joy of the Lord has done this for me.

name: Ayọ̀olúwatómi
meaning: The joy of God is sufficient for me.

name: Ayọ̀olúwayímiká
meaning: The joy of the lord surrounds me.
extended meaning: This is an expanded form of Yímiká or "Yínká"

name: Ayọ̀súnkànmí
meaning: Joy has moved close to me.

name: Ayọ̀tálẹ́
meaning: Joy is sufficient into the future.

name: Ayọ̀tọ̀míwá
meaning: Joy traced its way back to me.

name: Ayọ̀ọbadé
meaning: The joy of the king has come.

name: Ayọ̀ọláolúwakìítán
meaning: The joy of God's wealth never end.

name: Ayọ́bíojo
meaning: He who sneak like a coward.

name: Ayọṣiku
meaning: Joy remains (in the future). There's still happiness ahead.
extended meaning: User comment: "We went through a lot of ups and downs (myself and my husband) before I had my son (Ayọ̀ṣìkù) but before I gave birth to him, things changed for good so my husband decided to give him that name."

name: Ààrẹ
extended meaning: Aàrẹ is a title, usually in the military of the Yoruba warriors company. The leader of the company from a clan takes the title when they join up with a coalition.

name: Àánúolúwapọ̀
meaning: The mercies of God are abundant.

name: Àárínọlá
extended meaning: A name given to a middle child, sometimes as a nickname.

name: Àbádùnmí
extended meaning: It's a name given to a child born in miraculous circumstances, signifying the thankfulness for escaping a negative outcome.

name: Àbákẹ́
extended meaning: It's an oriki (a yoruba ancestral pet name).

name: Àbánikándá
extended meaning: The full aphorism says "The ant can only plot, it can not eat into stone."

name: Àbáyọ̀mí
extended meaning: It is a name given to a child born after a number of unfortunate or near unfortunate circumstances. It is often called in full as Àbáyòmí Olúwaniòjé: I would have been mocked, if not for God.

name: Àbídẹ́kun
extended meaning: This is typically given to a child born with the intention of not having another one after him/her.

name: Àbíyè
meaning: One who is given birth to who lives.

name: Àbẹ̀bí
meaning: Someone (usually female) born after a lot of persuasion.

name: Àbẹ̀fẹ́
meaning: One begged to love, one whom you begged before she loves/marry you.
extended meaning: Similar to Àbẹ̀kẹ́. Typical Yoruba name without religious input. Usually female name.

name: Àbẹ̀gbé
meaning: The one we begged to carry.

name: Àbẹ̀jẹ́
meaning: One who one has to plead with to answer.

name: Àbẹ̀kẹ́
meaning: One begged to pet, care for.

name: Àbẹ̀ní
extended meaning: This is a cognomen, oríkì. This is typically a feminine name.

name: Àbọ̀ábá
meaning: We're coming home to meet him/her.

name: Àdábánìjà
meaning: You don't know how brave you are until you're confronted by conflict.

name: Àdìgún
extended meaning:
"This is a great name that Yorùbá people seem so fit to call the God almighty." - user feedback.

It is also a common cognomen, oríkì.

name: Àdùbí
extended meaning: This is a cognomen given to children also named Ìgè, because they were born via breech birth. But Àdùbí is often given to female children while Ìgè is given to male children.

name: Àdùfẹ́
meaning: One that many people want to date/marry/love.

name: Àdùkẹ́
meaning: One we eagerly compete to care for. A highly beloved one. People fight over the privilege to pamper her.

name: Àdùkẹ́adé
meaning: We compete in our care for the king/prince. The king/prince is well loved.

name: Àdùnní
meaning: The one pleasant to have. Sweet personality.

name: Àdúràtọ́lá
meaning: Prayer is as valuable as wealth/success/nobility.

name: Àdùní
meaning: 1. A joy to have. 2. One we struggled to have.

name: Àgàgú
extended meaning: If you know what this name means, please supply by using the "improve this entry" button.

name: Àgbétù
meaning: The worship of the Àgbé divinity is consoling.

name: Àgbétúnsìn
meaning: The Àgbé divinity is worth worshiping.

name: Àgbétúyì
meaning: The Àgbé divinity is worth value.

name: Àgbòméjì
extended meaning: The common saying from where this name comes says "Àgbò méjì kò lè mu omi nínu koto", meaning "Two rams cannot drink from the same pot at the same time." The name seems like one borne out of a major conflict.

name: Àgbẹ̀bíyí
meaning: The farmer gave birth to this.

name: Àgbẹ́tómilóyè
meaning: Farming is equivalent to royalty to me.

name: Àgùdà
meaning: The name has been used to refer to the Afro-Brazilian returnees to Lagos in the late 19th Century who headed the Roman-Catholic churches (even though most of them retained their Òrìṣà-worshipping backgrounds). The name first came into use in Lagos around 1835 when the first wave of returnees came into town.
extended meaning: The meaning of the word itself hasn't yet been ascertained.

name: Àìná
meaning: Àìná is the name of a female (or sometimes male) child born with the umbilical cord around his or her neck. In most cases, though, the male equivalent is named Òjọ́.
extended meaning: Àìná is an orúkọ àmútọ̀runwá ("name that is brought from heaven", usually given to a child based on the circumstances of their birth). Àìná has special oríkì (praise or poetry) that says: Àìná ò r'ósùn.

name: Àíkí
meaning: Someone with a prominent role (worthy of being greeted by prostrating).
extended meaning:
'It is formerly called "Àyíkí: (a person you roll on the ground when you greet). 

The person that was first called the name is a warrior, hunter and herbalist. He always wins whenever he goes to war, so whenever they're back from the war, people troop out to welcome them. In the process, the will prostrate and start rolling on the ground. So whenever people want to describe him, the will say the man we roll on the ground to greet (Bàbá tí a máa ń yí kí). Thus Baba Àyíkí.

The "Y" was removed later by his descendants, thus it is only Àíkí now.'

Submission by Olúṣọlá Àíkí

name: Àjàdí
meaning: One who fights to repair. [Verification needed]

name: Àjàláyé
meaning: The loft of the earth. [verification needed]
extended meaning: This is one of the nicknames of the Ọọ̀nis of Ifẹ

name: Àjàlá
meaning: One who has fought and survived.

name: Àjàntálá
meaning: A problem child, as described in the novel Ògbójú Ọdẹ Nínú Igbó Irúnmalẹ̀.

name: Àjàyí
meaning: A child born face upwards (i.e. the occiput posterior position)

name: Àjàṣorò
meaning: One who fights while making sacrifices to Orò deity. [verification needed]
extended meaning: The popular nickname for the Princess Mọremí.

name: Àjájá
meaning: One who fights in the war.

name: Àjìún
meaning: A child over whom one rejoices.

name: Àjíhún
meaning: One that one wakes up to celebrate.

name: Àjíkẹ́
meaning: One who wakes up to petting/care/cherishing.
extended meaning: It's a cognomen, oríkì, usually for girlchildren.

name: Àjùmọ̀bí
meaning: One born of a number of people.

name: Àjànàkú
extended meaning:
We can not infer the meaning from the morphology. It is an onomatopoeic name used to refer to the size and enormity of the elephant, or the person so-named.

"Àjànàkú kọ já mo rí n kan fìrí..." meaning the elephant/ great one cannot pass unnoticed.

name: Àjàtóntìrìàjàbalẹ̀
meaning: The roof that pushes/crushes other roofs (down).
extended meaning: It's an adulatory name used to describe the ancestral warriors of Òmù-Àrán in Ìgbómìnà.

name: Àjùlọolúwa
extended meaning: This is a modern Christian name.

name: Àjọkẹ́
extended meaning: Àjọkẹ́ is a cognomen usually given to female children.

name: Àkanní
meaning: One that is special to have.

name: Àkànfẹ́
extended meaning:
A cognomen.
Compare: Àkànbí or Àdùfẹ́.

name: Àkànkẹ́
extended meaning: It is a pet name, a cognomen.

name: Àkànmú
extended meaning: The name is a cognomen, oríkì. See Àkànkẹ́.

name: Àkékùejò
meaning: The surviving half of a sundered snake.

name: Àkẹ́rà
meaning: One who is cared for to a fault.

name: Àlàbánwò
meaning: The Àlà deity should watch over the child.

name: Àlàbá
extended meaning: It is the name given to the fourth child after a Táíwò, Kẹ́hìndé and Ìdòwú

name: Àlàbí
meaning: One born to the white cloth (of Ọbàtálá)
extended meaning:
It's a cognomen, an oríkì.
See also: Tàlàbí.
gloss: [{'alà': ' - white cloth of Ọbàtálá, the Yorùba god of creation and creativity'}]

name: Àlàdé
meaning: HOMOGRAPH 1. One who survives to arrive. (Àlàdé) 2. The white cloth (of Ọbàtálá) arrives (Àlàdé) 3. Prince (Aládé)

name: Àlàó
meaning: One destined to divide and conquer his/her enemies.

name: Àlùfá
extended meaning: Likely a Yorubanized version of an Arabic title for priest "Alfa".

name: Àlùkò
meaning: The name of a rare bird.

name: Àlàáfíàbámi
meaning: I am at peace. I have peace. I am definitely without trouble or chaos.

name: Àmókèọjà
meaning: One who earns the best of everything. [rough translation. See extra information below]
extended meaning:
"One who held (or holds on) to the upper side of the market. This could be the name a warrior who fought and prevailed, holding on to a segment of community land separated by the market."

"Àmóke-means One that takes the top or comes out with the best.

ọjà-means market, goods, wares or something of value.

Àmókèọjà
The one that takes the top of the market (transliteration).

The one that takes the best of good things or something very close."

name: Àmọ̀kẹ́
meaning: To know (her) is to care for (her).

name: Àmọ̀pé
meaning: 1. One whose knowledge is complete. 2. One we know completely.

name: Ànjọláọlọ́run
meaning: We're enjoying the wealth of God.

name: Ànútọ̀míwá
meaning: Mercy looked for me. Mercy found me.

name: Àńrọ́láolúwayọ̀
meaning: We are seeing the glory/wealth of God and we are rejoicing.

name: Àpèjoyè
meaning: One called to be ennobled by chieftaincy.

name: Àpèkẹ́
extended meaning: This is a cognomen, oríkì. Feminine.

name: Àràbà
meaning: 1. A chieftaincy title in Òṣogbo 2. The oak tree.

name: Àràirenimí
meaning: I am made of good wonders.

name: Àránsíọlá
meaning: A nobility that is well targetted.

name: Àrìnpéọlá
meaning: One who walks well into honour.

name: Àríkẹ́
meaning: One that is cared for on sight.

name: Àríyọ̀osù
meaning: One seen with joy, like a new moon.

name: Àrẹbí
meaning: The chief gave birth to. [verification needed]

name: Àrẹbíyí
meaning: The chief gave birth to this.

name: Àrẹ̀mú
meaning: One that needs to be petted into action.
extended meaning: It is a cognomen meaning something like someone whose oríkì you must render before he can agree to run an errand for you.

name: Àsìkòtolúwalójù
meaning: God's time is best. Everything is beautiful in God's time

name: Àsùnlé
meaning: 1. One worthy of being displayed (as beautiful) when asleep. 2. One beautiful enough to invite being slept on. 3. A dependable personality.
extended meaning: As cognomen, oríkì, usually for women.

name: Àsùnmọ́
meaning: A common Yorùbá oríki, likely meaning someone that you like to be with or be around.

name: Àsẹ̀hìndè
extended meaning: "Sẹ̀hìndè" means to take care of the home in someone else's absence. This name is given to a child designated as the person who would play that role in the absence (or demise) of the parents.

name: Àtúnbí
meaning: The reincarnated one. The reborn one.

name: Àtẹ́wọ́lará
extended meaning: The general implication of this name is that hard work pays. And by hard work, since Yorùbá traditional cultures were agrarian, they mean 'farm work' which is done with the hands/palms. In other words, even if you have no one, you will always have your hands as kin, and that will get you through everything.

name: Àtẹ́wọ́logún
meaning: In one's palm is one's inheritance.
extended meaning: It means only your hard-work can give you wealth.

name: Àwòfẹ́
meaning: Loved at first-sight! Beloved! Look and love!

name: Àwẹ̀ní
meaning: A child to be bathed and possessed.

name: Àwẹ̀ró
meaning: One bathed and covered in wrappers.

name: Àyàngbémisọ́lá
meaning: Drumming put me into this place of honour.

name: Àyàngbẹ̀yẹ
meaning: The drummer received respect and honour.

name: Àyàntókun
meaning: The drummer is as large as the sea.

name: Àyàntóyè
meaning: The drummer is prominent enough for honour.

name: Àyánbímpé
meaning: I was born into a family of drummers, and I was born perfect.

name: Àyándéọ́lá
meaning: The spirit of the drummer has arrived into success.

name: Àyándọlápọ̀
meaning: The spirit of the drummer brings nobility together.

name: Àyánfowórà
meaning: (A drummer) got this child at a high cost.
extended meaning:
"Fowórà" is usually given to children whose conception, pregnancy or birth was troublesome for the parents, and cost them a lot of money (for physicians).

See also: Adéfowórà, Oyèfowórà.

name: Àyánlọ́wọ̀
gloss: [{'àyàn': ' - the drummer, the spirit of the drum'}]

name: Àyánwùmí
meaning: I'm beloved by (the spirit of) drumming.
gloss: [{'àyàn': ' - the drummer, the spirit of drumming'}]

name: Àyìnlá
meaning: A child meant to be praised, fetted, and disciplined.

name: Àyándìran
meaning: Drumming has become a family heritage/ is hereditary.
gloss: [{'àyàn': ' - the spirit of drumming, the drummer'}]

name: Àyángbọlá
meaning: The drummer has been given riches/glory/nobility.

name: Àyánṣẹ́gun
extended meaning: The word "àyán" root is usually added to names of children born into the lineage of drummers.

name: Àyọ̀ní
extended meaning: This name is a cognomen, oríkì

name: Àánúolúwabòmí
meaning: I am covered /protected with mercy of God.

name: Àṣàkẹ́
meaning: Selected, picked to be pampered or cherished.

name: Àṣekún
meaning: What is done in addition to another. Full name: Àṣekúnlowó (money is only worth adding to, via hard work).

name: Àṣekúnlowó
gloss: [{'àṣekún': ' - something you work in order to add to'}]

name: Álímì
meaning: Yorùbá's version of the Arabic name "Aleem", meaning 'knowledgeable' or 'learned' or 'wise'.
extended meaning: It is also one of the 99 names of God in Islam.

name: Á̀ṣáwògbínkọ́rọ́
meaning: The hawk looks at the snail with side-eyes.
extended meaning:
The full name is actually an adage (áṣà wò ígbín kọ́rọ, ìkáráwùn o ṣẹ́ẹ́ ṣà)
The hawk looks at the snail with side-eyes because its shell can't be pecked at.

name: Aṣebíọ̀yọ́
meaning: One who behaves like an Ọ̀yọ́ person.

name: Aṣebíọmọ
extended meaning: "In Yorubaland, it is believed that children are the succor of the elderly, and blessed is he whose quiver is full of them. So the name could probably also be interpreted as "He/she who brings comfort like a child."

name: Aṣímọlówó
meaning: One who counts his/her children as if counting money. (Basically, blessed with so many children s/he does a lot of kid-counting).

name: Aṣíwájú
extended meaning: "It's also a war title of the chief of the unit that fights at the head of the army."

name: Aṣúbíaró
meaning: One as dark as the dye.

name: Aṣọláyídé
meaning: One who makes wealth/success come around.

name: Aṣọ́nibárẹ́
meaning: One who watches (is careful about) whom he/she befriends.

name: Babábuyìkúnmi
meaning: Father (God) has added honour to me.

name: Babádáràọláfúnmi
meaning: Father created wonders of wealth for me.

name: Babádé
extended meaning: When a man's father is late, and such a man eventually has a male child, the name Babádé. See: Babátúndé.

name: Babáfèyídámilọ́lá
meaning: God (or Father) blessed me with this.

name: Babágbèmí
meaning: HOMOGRAPH 1. Father(hood) benefits me. 2. Father(hood) carried me.

name: Babálétí
extended meaning:
The implication of the name could be that the child's father (or a recently departed ancestor) harkened to the family's prayer. "Has hearing" may mean "to have empathy."

See: Ifálétí/Fálétí

name: Babáníyì
meaning: Father possesses honour. Fatherhood is honourable.

name: Babárímisá
meaning: Father saw me and ran away.
extended meaning: A name given to a child born almost immediately after his father's (or grandfather's) demise.

name: Babátúnbọ́lá
meaning: Father gave birth to wealth again.

name: Babátọ̀míwá
meaning: The father has come to me.

name: Babátọ́lá
meaning: Being a father is glorious. Being the head of a family is honourable. The head of the family is as valuable as riches.

name: Babátọ́pẹ́
meaning: Father is worth being thankful for.
extended meaning: Can also be seen as a contraction of "Bàbá tó fún l'ọ́pẹ́" which would mean Father or God is worth giving praise to.

name: Babáyẹjú
meaning: Father excused himself (left). This name is given to a child born shortly after the demise of a family patriarch. Compare: Babátúndé, Babárínsá.
extended meaning: This name is given to a child born shortly after the demise of a family patriarch. Compare: Babátúndé, Babárínsá.

name: Babáyẹmí
meaning: Fatherhood befits me. Father is worthy of me.

name: Babájídé
extended meaning: It is usually given to son born after the death of a father or grandfather. This is similar to names like Babátúndé, Babárìndé etc.

name: Babárìndé
meaning: Father walked in. Father walked our way. Father came in on foot.
extended meaning: On November 19, 2016, at Aké Arts and Book Festival, writer Ngugi Wa Thiong'o was christened "Babárìndé" for his fatherly role, work in African literature, and pioneering reputation in indigenous language literature.

name: Babátúndé
extended meaning: This name is usually given to a child born after the passing of either a father or a grandfather in the family, signifying a return.

name: Baiyékùsí
meaning: What is left of the world.

name: Bamicole
meaning: Viens m aider à construire ma maison. [voir Bámikọ́lé]

name: Bangoché
meaning: This name used in cuban orisa tradition is derived from the Yorὺbá name Bámgbós̩é. Bámgbós̩é means "carry the os̩é for me." An os̩é is a double-edged axe of the thunder and rain deity S̩àngó.

name: Bàbámọlé
meaning: Father knows the house/home. Father found his way home.
extended meaning: Likely a name given to a child born after the death of a grandfather. See also: Babátúndé or Babáwálé.

name: Bàjò
extended meaning: This is a common short form of Adébàjò, Ọṣìnbàjò, etc.

name: Báatifẹ́órí
meaning: As we wanted it to be (that's how it is).

name: Bádérìnwá
meaning: One who walks in with royalty.

name: Bámbọ̀
extended meaning: A short form of Adébámbọ̀, or Olúbámbọ̀, etc.

name: Bámgbáiyé
meaning: Live in this world with me.
extended meaning: The name is typically given to babies whose mothers have a history of their babies dying at birth or stillbirths: also called àbíkú children.

name: Bámgbálà
meaning: Help me carry the white cloth of purity.
extended meaning: The àlà is a traditional white cloth of the Ọbàtálá religious worship.

name: Bámgbáyé
meaning: Join me to live in the world.
extended meaning: It's a name given usually to àbíkú children.

name: Bámgbọ́pá
meaning: Help me carry the staff (or the Ọ̀pá deity).
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Bámidúró
meaning: Wait with me. Stay with me.

name: Bámigbégbìn
meaning: Assist me to carry the Igbìn. (the drum beaten in the worship of Òrìṣàálá/Ọbàtálá deity).
extended meaning:
This is a name borne by drummers for Òrìsálá worship. 
Compare: Bámgbóṣé, for Ṣàngó worshippers.

name: Bámigbọ́pá
meaning: Help me carry the staff (of the Ọ̀pá deity)
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Bámikọ́láwọlé
meaning: Help bring honor and wealth into home.

name: Bámilọ́shìn
meaning: Join me in owning the Ọṣìn deity.
extended meaning: The meaning of Ọṣìn has been debated. It has been said to mean either of "king" or "child" or a specific deity peculiar to Ìjẹ̀bú people.

name: Bámimọ́rẹ́
extended meaning: It's a name from the Òkè-Ògùn Region of Oyo State.

name: Bámisé
extended meaning:
The name is a supplication to the creator.
See also: Bámiṣayé.

name: Bámishígbìn
meaning: Help me celebrate (with the Ìgbìn drums).

name: Bámishílé
meaning: Help me/join me open a house.

name: Bámisílé
extended meaning: This is a name given to the first child born in a new house. Similar to "Kọ́láwọlé"

name: Bámitálẹ́
meaning: Stay with me till the evening (of life).
extended meaning: This is also an àbíkú name, given to children to entreat them from leaving early. See also: Bámikalẹ́/Bánkalẹ́.

name: Bámitẹ́fa
meaning: Help me spread the Ifá mat; join me in Ifá practice.

name: Bámitẹ́kọ̀
meaning: Literal: Help me lay sealants on the floor of my boat/vehicle. Figurative: Support me. Help me succeed.
extended meaning: The name is typically found among people whose ancestral occupation was making canoes.

name: Bámitọ́lá
meaning: 1. Help me taste wealth. 2. Help me match wealth.

name: Bángbọ́fá
meaning: Help me listen to the Ifá.

name: Bángbọ́pá
meaning: Help me lift a staff (or the Òrìṣà Oko).
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Bánjókò
extended meaning: A better way of writing the name, suited to the phonological underlining, would be "Bánjókòó".

name: Bánkẹ́
extended meaning: The full name can be Olúbánkẹ́, Adébánkẹ́, etc.

name: Bánmẹ́kẹ́
meaning: Help me hold the house pillars.

name: Bánúsọ
meaning: Dialogue (only) with yourself (rather than with others).
extended meaning: Full saying: Bá'nú sọ, má rò f'énìyàn.

name: Bánwò
meaning: Help me look after... Shortened form of Adébánwò, Ọlábánwò, Olúbánwò.
gloss: [{'bá': ' - to help, if, to meet on arriving to a place etc'}]

name: Báòkú
extended meaning: This name is a shortened form of a longer Yorùbá proverb "B'á ò kú, ìse ò tán", meaning, "as long as we're alive, there is hope."

name: Báyìlolútó
meaning: This shows how great God is.

name: Báyọ̀
extended meaning: A common short form of a longer name. See: Báyọ̀dé, Adébáyọ̀, Olúbáyọ̀dé, etc

name: Bádéjọ
meaning: Be at one with the crown.

name: Bákàrè
extended meaning: This is the nickname of the first Caliph of Islam. Abubakr, Abubakar. Originally Arabic, the 'Abu' part is dispensed with, and the 'bakar' part gets a terminal vowel according to Yoruba morphological patterns. Culled from www.farooqkperogi.com

name: Bámgbóṣé
meaning: Help me carry the (Ṣàngó's) double-headed wand.
extended meaning: 'The name Bámgbóṣé (is) obviously connected with Ṣàngó, the Yorùbá god of thunder. The association with Ṣàngó is further strengthened by the names given to my father and his elder brother. He was Ṣàngódípẹ̀ while his brother was Ṣàngodèyí. It is interesting to note that wherever the name...is found, either in Yorùbáland or in the Yorùbá Diaspora in Bahia, Brazil, the appellation ascribed to it is the same, i.e. Bámgbóṣé Ọ̀rọ́bìtìkó, "Bámgbóṣé, who rolls in opulence." Obviously, the original bearer of that name must have been a corpulent person!' - Professor Ayọ̀ Bámgbóṣé (From Grace to Grace: An Autobiography).

name: Bámiṣayé
meaning: Come enjoy the world with me.

name: Bánjí
extended meaning: The name will often be prefixed with Olú or Ọlá.

name: Bárátúndé
meaning: 1. When the relatives returned. 2. When the bodies return. 3. When wonders return. (Baràtúndé)

name: Baṣọ̀run
meaning: The general, head of ọṣọ̀run. [verification needed]
extended meaning: This is the title given to the highest military general in Ibadan.

name: Bétikú
meaning: As long as he/she doesn't die.
extended meaning: This is a name given to àbíkú children. See also: Bíòbákú

name: Béyìòkú
meaning: If this one did not die.
extended meaning: This is an àbíkú name. See also: Bétikú, Bíòbákú.

name: Biléwará
meaning: One adored by all kith and kin.

name: Bíálà
extended meaning: The àlà white cloth is a symbol of the creation god Ọbàtálá, so the name is traced to the devotees of this deity.

name: Bíbíire
extended meaning: This name is taken from a common Yorùbá saying, "Bíbíire kò ṣeé fi owó rà", meaning "Good birth can't be bought."

name: Bíbílarí
meaning: It's only his/her birth that we've seen.

name: Bímbọ́lú
meaning: I was given birth to with heroism, prominence.

name: Bímotifẹ́lolúwáṣe
meaning: God has given me my heart desire.

name: Bímpé
meaning: Shortened form of: Adébímpé Ọlábímpé Oyèbímpé Àyánbímpé Olúbímpé

name: Bínáwọlé
extended meaning: Bí iná wọlé òkùnkùn á paradà.

name: Bínútirí
extended meaning: Full proverb: "Bí inú ti rí ni obì í yàn: As the mind is, so is the divination patterns of the kola."

name: Bíòkú
extended meaning: This is a name for àbíkú children, gambling on the likelihood of their survival.

name: Bísálà
extended meaning: The àlà white cloth is a symbol of the creation god Ọbàtálá, so the name is traced to the devotees of this deity.

name: Bísọ́dún
meaning: (A child) Given birth to during festivities.

name: Bíòbákú
extended meaning: This is a name for àbíkú children, betting on the possibility of their survival.

name: Bolúwatitó
meaning: (Look at) How great as God is.

name: Bólódeòkú
meaning: If the owner of the house isn't dead...(his house won't grow weeds).
extended meaning: The full Yorùbá proverb says "B'ólóde ò kú, òde ò wu gbẹ́gi."

name: Bólújí
meaning: 1. Wakes up with prominence. 2. Wakes up with God.

name: Bólújọ
meaning: Be at one with the prominent one.

name: Bólúmọlé
meaning: 1. Build a bouse with God. Build a house with the prominent one. Build a house with the master. 2. Go with God/Prominent one/master, to know the house.

name: Bólúwadé
meaning: One who came with the lord.

name: Bórìshàdé
meaning: One who comes with the Orìṣà.

name: Bórítifẹ́lolúṣe
meaning: God has done exactly as one's head/destiny wishes him to do.

name: Bósòro
meaning: When the going gets tough. [verification needed]

name: Bóyè
extended meaning:
A commonly abridged form of a longer name.
See: Adébóyè, Bóyèdé, Bóyèjọ, etc

name: Bóyèwá
meaning: Came at the same time as a promotion (or a new appointment etc).

name: Bólúwatifẹ́
meaning: As the lord wants. As God pleases.

name: Bùsúyì
extended meaning: A short form of Olúbùsúyì, Adébùsúyì, etc

name: Bùsọ́lámi
extended meaning: This is a short form of a longer name like Adébùsọ́lámi, Olúbùsọ́lámi, etc

name: Búkì
meaning: Shortened form of: Olúwabùkọ́lá Adébùkọ́lá Oyèbùkọ́lá

name: Búsàrí
meaning: Yorúbá's version of the Arabic name "Al-Basri".
extended meaning: Taken from the name of a Muslim thinker Hassan Al-Basri. He is from Basra somewhere in the present day Iraq.

name: Bádéwò
meaning: Give birth to royalty to see how it will be/look.

name: Bájọmọ
meaning: 1. The king resembles the son. The father resembles the son. 2. The king is bigger than the son. The father is bigger than the son.

name: Bámikalẹ́
meaning: Stay with me till my old age.

name: Bísígà
meaning: A child who was birth in the palace.

name: Bólókundé
meaning: A child born at the period of Olókun Festival.

name: Bẹ́kọ̀
extended meaning: The phonetic spelling of the name, more accurate, is Bẹ́ẹ̀kọ́.

name: Bọ̀dé
extended meaning: This is a common short form of Olábọ̀dé, Olúbọ̀dé, Akínbọ̀dé, etc

name: Bọ̀rọ̀kìnní
extended meaning: An onomatopoeic name with no internal meaning. Used as cognomen.

name: Bọ̀wálé
extended meaning: Short form of Adebọ̀wálé, Oyèbọ̀wálé, etc

name: Bọ́dúndé
meaning: Comes with the year (or with festivities).

name: Bọ́dúnjóko
meaning: A child at one with festivities.
extended meaning: Given to a child born during festivities. See also: Bọ́dúndé, Bọ́dúnwá.

name: Bọ́dúnrìn
meaning: One who comes with the season.

name: Bọ́gunbọ́lù
meaning: One who feeds the war camp and the whole town.

name: Bọ́jọ́dé
meaning: Came with the day. Arrived with a (good/momentous) day.

name: Bọ́látitó
meaning: (Check out) how big/much our wealth/success is.

name: Bọ́láwáyé
meaning: Emerge into the world with nobility.

name: Bọ́ládalẹ́
meaning: Go with nobility until till the end.

name: Bọ́lọ́mọpé
extended meaning: This is a name given, usually, to a child whose birth wipes off the tears and blemish of the parents who had been considered incapable of being parents.

name: Bọ́lọ́runòsífúnwa
meaning: If God be not for us.

name: Damilọ́lá
extended meaning: A common short form of Olúwadámilọ́lá.

name: Dayọ̀
extended meaning:
Shortened form of:

Adédayọ̀
Olúwádayọ̀
Tèmídayọ̀
Ìfẹ́dayọ̀
Oládayọ̀
Olúdayọ̀

name: Dàda
extended meaning: This is one of the names called àmútọ̀runwá (brought from heaven).

name: Dáhùnsí
extended meaning: This is a shortened version of a longer name, like Ifádáhùnsi (Ifá responded/manifested).

name: Dáìró
extended meaning: It's a name given to a child considered to be an Àbíkú to keep them from going away.

name: Dáìsí
extended meaning: This is a name given to an àbíkú child.

name: Dáraníjọ
meaning: Good in company: [A shortened form of "Adáraníjọ"]

name: Dárasími
extended meaning: A shortened form of Ọlúwadárasími: the lord has been good to me.

name: Dárópalé
meaning: Make dye to beautify the house.

name: Dáwódù
extended meaning: This is a name given typically to the first son in a family.

name: Dáṣàólú
meaning: Make beauty for the prominent one.

name: Dáramọ́lá
meaning: One who has achieved personal goodness along with wealth.

name: Dèjì
extended meaning: This is a common short form of Adédèji, Ọládèji, etc. See "Variants" for more.

name: Débọ̀
meaning: A common short form of Adébọ̀wálé.

name: Dédẹkẹ́
meaning: The crown becomes the pillar that hold up the house.

name: Défúnkẹ́
meaning: The crown gave me to cherish.

name: Dékúnlé
extended meaning: A common short form of Adékúnlé.

name: Délọ́dún
meaning: 1. The crown has festivity. 2. One who arrived during the festivity

name: Dénlóyè
meaning: 1. Cover me with honour. 2. My crown has honour.

name: Déńrelé
extended meaning: This name is typically given to a child born after the passing of a prominent member of the family, like a grandfather or grandmother.

name: Désálù
extended meaning: The story of the Désálù family of Abẹ́òkuta says that they used to be the crown-keeping family, but they fled during one prominent war so as to keep the crown safe. This period of flight is what influenced a change of name to Désálù.

name: Désọ́lá
meaning: 1. Arrive into wealth. 2. A short form of Adésọ́lá

name: Détayọ̀
meaning: 1. Arrive to sit with joy. 2. Royalty is worth celebrating (Adétáyọ̀)

name: Déwálé
meaning: A different way of writing Adéwálé.

name: Déyanjú
meaning: Short for Adéyanjú: the crown is complete.
extended meaning: The name doesn't mean much in this contracted form, but many have preferred to use it in this written form.

name: Déṣíkù
meaning: The crown opens a door (of wealth to me).
extended meaning: The name is from Usi Èkìtì.

name: Délànọ
meaning: The crown has opened the way.

name: Dìran
extended meaning: This is a short form of Adédìran, Olúdìran, Oyèdìran, etc.

name: Dídéolú
meaning: The arrival of a star. The arrival of a prominent one.

name: Dípẹ̀
extended meaning: There are many variations of this name, prefaced by Adé, Ọlá, Oyè, etc.

name: Dísù
extended meaning: The Arabic name is the name of an ancient prophet mentioned in the Qur'an (Qur'an 19:56-57 and Qur'an 21:85-86) and believed to be the same as Enoch in the bible.

name: Díẹ̀kọ́ladé
meaning: Royalty isn't inconsequential. The crown isn’t to be taken lightly.

name: Díẹ̀kọ́láolúwa
meaning: The goodies/grace/wealth from God is limitless.

name: Diẹ̀kọ́lọláolúwanínúayémi
meaning: The fortune of God in my life is not minute.

name: Dolúpọ̀
extended meaning:
Given to a child born into two strong families, or a child considered important in bringing two strong traits together.

See also: Dadépọ̀

name: Dossoumon
meaning: This is a French-African version of the Yorùbá name "Dòsùnmú".
extended meaning: The original name, spelt either as Dòsùmú or Dòsunmú, is a name common in the Lagos area, particularly among the ruling house. (See: Dòsùnmú). This French-African variation is common in Benin Republic, Togo, and every other place in French West Africa where Yorùbá emigration has taken root. The name was, for a while in colonial Nigeria, also spelt as Docemo.

name: Doyin
extended meaning: This is a short form of a longer name. e.g. Doyinsọ́lá.

name: Dòkun
extended meaning: This is a common short form.

name: Dòsùmú
meaning: Hold onto the sacred Òsùn staff.
extended meaning: This is a common royal name in Lagos and other parts of West Africa. it has been written in the colonial times as Docemo but also as Dossoumon in other parts of French West Africa. It most common (and most phonological) spelling is Dòsùnmú.

name: Dòsùnmú
meaning: Hold onto the sacred Òsùn staff.
