extended meaning: This is a common royal name in Lagos and other parts of West Africa. it has been written in the colonial times as Docemo and Dòsùmú, but also as Dossoumon in other parts of French West Africa. This is the most common (and most phonological) spelling.

name: Dòyìnbó
extended meaning: The Yorùbá fascination with Europeans led to names like this, the "òyìnbó" component signifying what the Yorùbá consider to be virtues.

name: Dùnmínínu
extended meaning: Likely a short form of Olúwadùnmínínú: the lord gladdens my heart.

name: Dùnní
extended meaning: A shortened form of a longer name: Adédùnní, Ọládùnní, Ìfẹ́dùnní, etc.

name: Dùńsìn
meaning: Sweet to worship (God is sweet to worship).

name: Dúdúlabí
meaning: We gave birth to the dark-skinned one.

name: Dúdúyẹmí
meaning: The dark skin is befitting of me.

name: Dúrógbọlá
extended meaning: This is an àbíkú name imploring the child to stay.

name: Dúrójaiyéọba
meaning: Wait to enjoy the life of a king.
extended meaning: This is likely an àbíkú name given to encourage the child to stay and not die.

name: Dúróoríkẹ́
meaning: Stay alive so that we may shower you with care.

name: Dúrótifá
extended meaning: This is a name given to a child considered to be an Àbíkú, asking him/her to stay because of the oracle.

name: Dúrówaiyé
extended meaning:
Traditionally given to àbíkú children.
See also: Dúrojaiyé.

name: Dúrówojú
meaning: Wait long enough to behold faces.

name: Dúróṣarọ́
meaning: Stay and to thrive as a blacksmith.
extended meaning: Name traditionally given to àbíkú children.

name: Dúróṣawo
meaning: Wait to participate in the Ifá priesthood.

name: Dúróṣọmọ
meaning: Stay long enough to become somebody.
extended meaning: This is an àbíkú name, entreating the child to wait past the early stages of life (when most àbíkú children die) so as to become somebody as an adult.

name: Dáre
meaning: Vindicate me. God has vindicated me (Olúdáre).

name: Démiládé
meaning: Crown me. Put a crown on my head.

name: Dídéolá
meaning: The arrival of wealth, nobility, and other good things.

name: Dòdóndáwà
extended meaning: Usually part of praise poetry, but is infrequently given as a proper name.

name: Dẹ̀hìndé
extended meaning: The full name can be Ọládẹ̀ìndé, Ọmọ́dẹ̀ìndé, Oyèdẹ̀ìndé, etc.

name: Dẹ̀hìntọ́
extended meaning: The name celebrates the eventual solution to an earlier problem. The full version can be one of Adédẹ̀hìntọ or Oládẹ̀hìntọ́, etc.

name: Dọlá
meaning: 1. Become wealth/success. 2. A short form of Adédọlá, Olúdọlá, Oyèdọlá, etc.

name: Dọlápọ̀
extended meaning: Name given to a child result of two Ọlá families marrying each other.

name: Dọ̀pámú
meaning: One who holds onto the staff of Òrìṣà oko.

name: Dọ̀pẹ̀mú
meaning: One who holds the ọ̀pẹ̀ (divination chain).

name: Dọ̀tun
extended meaning: This is a common shortened form of Adédọ̀tun, Oyèdọ̀tun, etc.

name: Ebígbọlá
extended meaning: A name given to a baby born during famine/drought.

name: Echu yinka
meaning: Practitioners of Cuban Orisa religion say this name means “the Elegguá (E̩lé̩gbáa) that watches the path.” It is derived from Ès̩úyín̄ká - Ès̩ù (the messenger deity) surrounds me.

name: Echualabi
meaning: Among Cuban users, the belief is that it means "the Echu (a deity) that divides births." In Yorùbá language, Ès̩ùlabí means "it is Ès̩ù that we gave birth to. "
extended meaning: Used among practitioners of Cuban Òrìṣà tradition, known alternately as Santería, Lucumí, or Regla de Ocha.

name: Echudina
meaning: In Cuban usage, the belief is that it means "Echu of the flame/fire." In Yorùbá language, "Ès̩údínà" means "Èṣú blocks the road (from enemies)."
extended meaning: This name is used among practitioners of the Òrìṣà tradition that developed in Cuba, formerly more commonly known as Santería and now known as Lucumí by modern practitioners. Practitioners of the Cuban Òrìṣà tradition no longer speak Yorùbá language outside of liturgical usage, so there is no understanding of the processes of assimilation and elision that occur in the Yorùbá language.  When practitioners see a name with "ina" at the end they assume it has to do with the Yorùbá word for "fire" - iná.

name: Echuyinka
meaning: Among practitioners of the Lucumí faith (formerly known as Santería), the belief is that Eshu Yinka means "the one (Eshu) that watches the road." This name is derived from the yorùbá "Ès̩ùúyínká" meaning, literally, "Ès̩ù (the yorùbá messenger deity) surrounds me." This can mean that the person was born into a family with many other devotees of the Yorùbá deity known as Èsù. It can also be a kind of prayer that Èsù surround and protect the individual.
extended meaning: The name is used in Cuba as well as in countries of the cuban diaspora such as Venezuela, Panama, Puerto Rico, United States, Spain, Mexico, among others.

name: Eégunjọbíẹ
meaning: The masquerade jointly gave birth to this.
extended meaning: Nombre religioso. Name commonly given in Latin America. A corruption of Eégúnjọbí.

name: Eégúnbiyì
meaning: The masquerade gave birth to value.
extended meaning: This isn't the same as Eégúnbíyìí.

name: Eégúnbíyìí
meaning: The masquerade gave birth to this (one).

name: Eégúnyẹmí
meaning: (Being with) masquerading has been beneficial to me.

name: Efunche
meaning: This is a name used among practitioners of cuban Òrìs̩à tradition, commonly know as Santería or Lucumí faith. The name is derived from the Yoruba name E̩fúns̩etán - E̩fun (white native chalk) is ready. Names beginning with e̩fun are often in reference to deities such as Olokun and Obatala or a number of other “white-cloth” deities of Yoruba Traditional Religion.
extended meaning: Efunche is the name of one of the founders of contemporary cuban Òrìs̩à religion.

name: Egúnjọbí
meaning: The masquerades gave birth to this.

name: Egúntọ́lá
extended meaning:
NOTE ON ORTHOGRAPHY

The proper way to write this name should be "Eégúntọlá" in order to allow for all the tone marks to be properly accounted for. However, most modern versions lose the first vowel, for ease of Anglophone writing, perhaps.

name: Egúnyìnmí
extended meaning: This is a name common to people from Eégun worshipping families.

name: Ejitọ́lá
meaning: Rain is enough for wealth (source of wealth).

name: Ejiyọóyè
meaning: The divinity of rain emerged in (our) honour.

name: Ejíbọ́dún
meaning: The rain (divinity) met a festival in progress.
extended meaning: See also: Olúbọ́dún, Adébọ́dún, Oyèbọ́dún, etc

name: Ejídé
extended meaning: Given to a child born during the raining season, or a child named to symbolise the beginning of torrential blessings.

name: Ejígbádéró
meaning: The (spirit of) rain upheld the crown.

name: Ejíwálé
extended meaning: People born at the height of the rainy season or born during a storm can be given this name.

name: Elébènlá
meaning: One who makes big heaps for farming.

name: Elégúndé
gloss: [{'oní': ' - the owner of, the bearer of'}]

name: Elétù
extended meaning: [If you know the meaning of this name, please send it to us via the "improve this entry" button]

name: Elúdiní
meaning: God comforted me. God strengthened me. God took care of me.

name: Elúfidípẹ̀
meaning: The slave used it for recompense.

name: Elúfidíyà
meaning: Elú used (this child or this occasion of the child's birth) for recompense.

name: Elúfowójù
meaning: The slave, because of riches, is great(er).
extended meaning: "Altogether it sounds rather arrogant, however when I pressed my dad several years ago with the same question he said our name simply means 'The Slave that rose from rags to riches'" - Femi Elúfowójù Jnr, actor-director and radio producer.

name: Elúfowórà
meaning: The one Elú bought with money.

name: Elúyẹlà
meaning: The slave is deserving of success.

name: Elúyẹra
meaning: The Elú person has left, departed.
extended meaning: The precise etymology of "elú" is unclear. But from word-of-mouth reports (see: Elúfowójù), one way of interpreting it is servitude (ẹrú), i.e. The name is derived from people freed from servitude at some point in the past. In the case of this particular name, a notable person from that lineage of Elú has just departed, hence the giving of the name to a new child. Like Babátúndé, the name submits to the belief of the Yorùbá in the continuation of life.

name: Eniìgbàlàolúwa
meaning: A person who brings God's Salvation.

name: Erinlẹ̀
meaning: A child born with placenta tied to his/her waist.

name: Erínjógunólà
meaning: The elephant lets the war survive.

name: Erínwọlé
extended meaning: It can also be interpreted as "The giant enters", since an elephant is a physical symbol of size and intimidation.

name: Eríyọmí
meaning: A dialectal variant of Oríyọmí: My personal god (orí) saved me.

name: Ewédọlá
meaning: The herbs have turned into riches.

name: Ewinletí
meaning: In Cuban usage, the belief is that it means "the ears of Obatala." In Yorùbá language, Iwínlétí means "the forest spirit/fairy (O̩bàtálá) has ears (listens to petitions)"
extended meaning:
In Cuban Òrìṣà tradition, ewin- and egüin- are used as prefixes for a number of names of Ọbàtálá initiates. Cuban practitioners believe that ewin- or egüin- means snail. 

This rendition is used among practitioners of cuban orisa tradition.

name: Ewúbàjò
extended meaning: See also: Adébàjò, Ọṣìnbàjò, Olúbàjò, etc

name: Eyínmẹ́nugún
meaning: The teeth makes the mouth straight.
extended meaning: A cognomen/nickname, given to one with well set dentition.

name: Èésúọlá
extended meaning: From Esúsú, a system of savings in which a bundle is given to each person at an allotted rotation.

name: Ègbèṣínà
meaning: Ègbè will open the way. Ègbè opened the way.

name: Èjíwùnmí
meaning: I am attracted to gap teeth.

name: Èjíwùmí
meaning: 1. I love tooth gaps 2. I love twins.

name: Èkémọdé
extended meaning: This is used to describe àbíkú children, born to die, with the belief that the child came only to die in infancy thus deceiving the parents. See also: Yémiítàn.

name: Èpédọlá
meaning: A curse placed (on us) turned beneficial instead.

name: Èrèọlá
meaning: The gains of success/wealth. The benefit of prominence.

name: Èròmídayọ̀
meaning: My thoughts have resulted in joy.

name: Èròmídọlá
meaning: My thought have turned to success.

name: Èyíloreolúwa
meaning: This is the gift of God

name: Èyímofẹ́
meaning: This one (is the one) I want.

name: Èyínimofé
meaning: This is what I want. This is whom I wanted. This is whom I love.

name: Èyíówùáwí
meaning: We do not wish to say this.
extended meaning: The full saying goes "Èyí ó wù á wí, t'Olúwa l'àṣẹ.

name: Èyítèmi
extended meaning: The name is popular name amongst the Itsekiri of Delta State.

name: Èyítóní
meaning: This child is the ultimate asset. This child is a valuable asset,

name: Èyíwùnmítólúwabunmí
meaning: I love what I've been given by God.

name: Èyítómi
meaning: This one is sufficient for me.

name: Èyítọ́lá
meaning: This is the worth of wealth.

name: Èṣùdé
meaning: Here comes Èsù, the Yorùbá trickster god.

name: Èṣúsànyà
meaning: Èṣù repaid me (with good) for my suffering.

name: Èṣúyẹmí
extended meaning: See also: Adéyẹmí, Olúyẹmí, Oyèyẹmí, etc.

name: Èṣúṣeékẹ́
meaning: (The child of) Èsù should be pampered.
extended meaning: It is beneficial to pamper Èsù (through this child).

name: Ganíyù
meaning: Yorùbá's version of the Arabic name "Ganiy" meaning wealthy.
extended meaning: Al-Ganiy is one of the 99 names of God in Islam.

name: Gbadéwọlé
meaning: Receive a crown with which to enter.

name: Gbanejọkẹ́
meaning: Two hundred people gathered to care for him/her. A multitude cares for him/her.

name: Gbangbalàṣá
meaning: The eagle is not afraid in the open field.

name: Gbaremiwá
meaning: Bring the goodness that belongs to me.

name: Gbàjàbíàmílà
meaning: One who, while fighting, pretends to be separating a fight.

name: Gbàyísomọ́rẹ
meaning: Have this tied to the gift.

name: Gbádégeṣin
meaning: Put the crown on the horse.

name: Gbélékalẹ̀
meaning: Erect a house. Build a home.

name: Gbéminíyì
extended meaning: Typically prefaced with Olú or Ọlá.

name: Gbénga
extended meaning: A common short form of Olúgbénga, Adégbénga, etc.

name: Gbémisọ́lá
meaning: Lift me into honour, wealth, nobility, success.

name: Gbogbolọmọ
meaning: No child of any gender is superior to the other.

name: Gbódórogun
meaning: One who carries a mortar into war.

name: Gbógunlórí
meaning: One with war constantly on his mind.

name: Gbólúwaga
extended meaning: This is a modern Christian name given in thanks for the child's birth or other corresponding happy circumstances.

name: Gbàyíṣemóre
meaning: This season or time favours me.
extended meaning: The name originated from Odo-Nla, a fishing community of Ugbo Kingdom in Ilaje L.G.A, Ondo State.

name: Gbádéwùnwọ́n
meaning: (We) make them envious of the (our) crown.

name: Gbénlé
extended meaning: This is a short form of Adégbénlé or Olúgbénlé

name: Gbénró
extended meaning: The longer form is Olúgbémiró, or Olúgbénró.

name: Gbẹ̀là
extended meaning: If you know the meaning of this name, please provide it using the "improve this entry" button above.

name: Gbọ́láyẹmí
meaning: Give me the courtesy I deserve. Make nobility fitting for me.
gloss: [{'gbé': ' - to lift, to carry, to reside'}]

name: Gbọ́láṣeré
meaning: (One who) has wealth to play around with.

name: Gbọ́tèmi
extended meaning: This is a short form of "Olúwagbọ́tèmi": The lord hears me.

name: Goríọlá
meaning: Climbed onto the top of wealth.

name: Gómìnà
extended meaning: This is a corruption of the English word "Governor".

name: Gígalolúwa
extended meaning: This name was given to a boy whose parent was barren for about five years before they gave birth to him. The name signifies the wonder of the parents at the miracle of his birth.

name: Hárúnà
meaning: Derived from the Arabic name "Harun" or "Haroon", which comes from the Hebrew name of Aaron (prophet).

name: Ibúọláshí
meaning: The deep ocean of success opened up.

name: Ibúọláṣí
meaning: The ocean of wealth has opened.

name: Ifábíyí
extended meaning: A more appropriate spelling would be "Ifábíyìí.

name: Ifádáìró
meaning: Ifá kept this from going away.
extended meaning: A name for a perceived àbíkú child, held back by the powers of Ifá from returning to the land of the dead.

name: Ifádáwọ́lémi
meaning: Ifá laid its hands on me.

name: Ifádilé
extended meaning: This is the full form of the name "Fádilé"

name: Ifádójú
meaning: Ifa has finally triumphed (come to a head).

name: Ifáfúnmi
meaning: Ifá gave me (this child) as a gift.

name: Ifáfọlábí
meaning: One born in a wealthy manner, place or time though Ifá.
extended meaning: Ọlá is also representative of more than just financial wealth. It can mean "success", or "notability" or even "nobility". See: http://blog.yorubaname.com/2016/12/12/ola-isnt-always-wealth/

name: Ifágbàmí
meaning: Ifa saved me. Ifa received me.

name: Ifágbẹ́núṣọlá
meaning: (This child of) Ifá creates nobility from within. Ifá makes nobility from inside the womb.
extended meaning: Another way to read this would be "Ifá depends on the soul to bring about nobility."
gloss: [{'ifá': ' - ọ̀rúnmìlà, Yorùbá god of intellect, knowledge, and wisdom'}]

name: Ifágbọ́láhàn
meaning: Ifá brought me into the limelight; exhibits its wealth (through me).

name: Ifájàre
meaning: Ifá is justified, is adjudged right.

name: Ifájímilà
meaning: Ifá let me live and/or prosper.

name: Ifájọkẹ́
meaning: One Ifá joins in to care for.

name: Ifájuyìgbé
meaning: Ifá did not let honour go to waste.

name: Ifájuyìtán
meaning: Ifá would not let honour finish.

name: Ifájùwọ́nlọ
meaning: Ifá is bigger than all of your enemies.

name: Ifáláyàjó
meaning: Ifá is brave enough to dance.

name: Ifápurọ́
meaning: 1. Ifa did not lie. 2. Ifa lied.

name: Ifáríbidó
meaning: Ifá has found a place to stay/settle.

name: Ifáríyìíkẹ
meaning: Ifá found this one to pet/love/take care of.

name: Ifárónbí
meaning: Ifá has found someone (good) to birth.

name: Ifáshadùn
extended meaning: The name comes from Ọ̀bàrà Lássùn in the Ifá corpus.

name: Ifáshayọ̀
meaning: 1. Ifá is joyful. 2. Ifá makes joy.

name: Ifásùnládé
meaning: Ifá mingles with royalty. Ifá sleeps on royalty. Ifá achieves royalty in his sleep.

name: Ifásọ̀ràntì
meaning: Ifa never fails to solve an issue.
extended meaning: The form of negation in this name confuses many people to pronounce it as the opposite of what it truly means. The practise of using a vowel to mark contrast and negation is common in Yorùbá and notable in this name. "Ifá à sọ ọ̀ràn tì" and not "Ifá sọ ọ̀ràn tì"

name: Ifásọ̀yíró
meaning: Ifá says this and it stands

name: Ifátógbiyèlé
meaning: "Ifa is worth resting on" or "Ifa is worthy to be praised"

name: Ifátókun
meaning: Ifá is as wide as the ocean.

name: Ifátósìn
meaning: Ifa is worthy to be worshipped.

name: Ifátúnmbí
meaning: Ifá has given me a second birth.

name: Ifátẹ́gbẹ́
meaning: Ifá matches up with its contemporaries.

name: Ifáṣadé
meaning: Ifá makes royalty. Ifá is behaving in a royal way. Ifá achieved royalty.

name: Ifáṣebé
meaning: Ifá fulfilled its promise (to me). Ifá did what it said it would.

name: Ifáṣeun
meaning: 1. Ifá has done well. 2. We thank Ifá.

name: Ifáṣèyífúnmi
meaning: The oracle has done this one for me

name: Ifáṣẹ̀yìn
meaning: Ifá acts well in one's absence.

name: Ifábùnmi
extended meaning: User comment: "My daughter received this name in Ibadan during her naming ceremony in association with Odù Ọ̀bàrà-Rẹtẹ̀. E se o"

name: Ifáfúnwá
meaning: Ifa gave me to look for.

name: Ifágúnwà
meaning: Ifá holds court. Ifá reigns. Ifá ascends the throne.

name: Ifájẹ́mirókun
meaning: Ifa lets me see the ocean

name: Ifájẹ́miróyè
meaning: Ifa lets me see the chieftaincy.

name: Ifákáyọ̀dé
meaning: Ifa has brought joy in droves.

name: Ifáloyè
meaning: Ifa is honour. Ifá is prestigious. Ifá is the ultimate title.

name: Ifámoríyọ̀
meaning: Ifa is what is making me happy.

name: Ifámosìnpẹ́
meaning: Ifa is what I've worshipped for a long time.

name: Ifáníran
meaning: 1. (My) Ifa has (is) heritage/legacy/lineage/ancestry/vision .. 2. Ifá has memory / Ifá remembers.

name: Ifátádé
meaning: Ifá is big enough for a crown. Ifá is as prominent as royalty.

name: Ifátólú
meaning: Ifa is big enough as a leader.

name: Ifátọba
meaning: Ifa is big enough for a king.

name: Ifátọ́lá
meaning: Ifa is big enough for wealth.

name: Ifádoyin
meaning: Ifá has become (as sweet as) honey.

name: Ifádáyìsí
meaning: Ifá preserved this (child). Ifá spared this.

name: Ifádìran
meaning: Ifá has become (part of) our ancestry.

name: Ifádókun
meaning: Ifá has become (as mighty/prominent as) the ocean.

name: Ifádúnkẹ́
meaning: It is joyful to care for Ifá ('s child).

name: Ifádọ́wọ́lé
meaning: Ifá laid hands on this (child for protection).

name: Ifáfúnmilólú
meaning: Ifá made me a leader. Ifá gave me a leader.

name: Ifáfọ́re
meaning: Ifá proclaimed goodness. Ifá has spoken well.

name: Ifájùbẹ́
meaning: Ifa is much more (than you can ever imagine)

name: Ifákóredé
meaning: Ifá brought good luck. Ifá brought me good luck.

name: Ifálorí
meaning: Ifá is my head || Ifá o senhor da minha cabeça

name: Ifálàmí
meaning: Ifá made me rich/wealthy. Ifá made me survive.

name: Ifálérí
meaning: 1. Ifá came out tops/is the winner. 2. Ifá promised, boasted.

name: Ifálòkun
meaning: Ifá is the ocean (is as wide, as deep, as bountiful as the ocean).

name: Ifámilékè
meaning: My Ifá is paramount. Meu Ifá acima de tudo!

name: Ifáróunbí
meaning: Ifa found (a child) to give birth to.

name: Ifásayọ̀
meaning: Ifâ brings me joy, I find joy in Ifá.

name: Ifátókẹ́
meaning: (The child of) Ifá is worth cherishing.

name: Ifáwáléọlá
meaning: Ifá enters the house of affluence.

name: Ifáṣeékẹ́
meaning: (The child of) Ifá is worthy of being pampered.

name: Ifẹ́tóní
meaning: It is good to be loved.

name: Igbókọ̀í
meaning: The bush has refused this one.
extended meaning:
Àbíkú name given in Benin Republic (Kétu/Ketou). 
See also: Igbókọ̀yí

name: Ijàọlá
meaning: The fight of wealth; the fight for wealth; the struggle for success/notabilty; the struggle between parts of a notable family (resulted in this)

name: Ikúenisáfun
meaning: One's death doesn't run from one.

name: Ikúènọ́mọre
meaning: Death doesn't have any good child.

name: Ikúgbàyígbé
meaning: Death did not take this completely.
extended meaning: This is a name given to a child born after a major death in the family.

name: Ikújọwọ́rẹ̀
meaning: Death, (please) drop his hands. Leave him be.

name: Ikúmápàyí
meaning: May death not kill this one.

name: Ikúòponíyì
meaning: Death did not take the prestigious one.

name: Ikúpọlátì
meaning: Death is unable to kill nobility.

name: Ikúshìmímọ̀
meaning: Death was confused and couldn't recognise me.

name: Ikúṣèrú
extended meaning: This is a name given to a family already scarred by the death of other children, or parents.

name: Ikújẹ́nyọ̀
extended meaning: A name given to àbíkú children in supplication for their life.

name: Ilarí ọbá
meaning: "Among the Lukumí in Cuba, this name has been retained. Its significance is understood to mean "King's (Shangó's) Messenger." It surely plays on the theme of the Ọ̀yọ́ palace Ìlàrís. It is accentuated according to Spanish grammatical dictates, as were all names in Cuba.'"
extended meaning: This is a name given to a member of the king group of servants mostly in Ọ̀yọ́.

name: Ilégbọnà
meaning: The home has space for artistry/beauty.

name: Ilésanmí
meaning: 1. I'm better off at home/hometown. 2. Home benefits me. Home befits me.

name: Ilúmọ̀ká
meaning: One known all around town. Famous.

name: Ilémobádé
meaning: I met the crown at home.

name: Iremofẹ́tidé
meaning: The goodness i crave has come.

name: Irenitèmi
meaning: Goodness is mine. May goodness come upon all that is mine. I have been blessed.

name: Ireolúwa
extended meaning: "Ire cannot be directly translated to English so easily. To fully understand Ire, one must include words like good fortune, blessings, serendipitous positive outcomes all wrapped in goodness!"

name: Ireolúwakànmí
meaning: The goodness of God has come to me.

name: Ireolúwamìdé
meaning: The goodness of my God has come.

name: Ireolúwatọ̀míwá
meaning: The goodness of the lord comes to me.

name: Ireolúwayànmífẹ́
meaning: God's goodness chose me to love.

name: Irewámiwá
meaning: Goodness has sought me forth or here.

name: Iréwámirí
meaning: Goodness has come to visit me.

name: Isíákà
meaning: From the Arabic form of Isaac.

name: Iwínjọbí
meaning: This child was given to us by spirit beings.

name: Iwínlẹ́yẹ
meaning: The worship of Iwin (fairies) is respectable.

name: Iwíndàpọ̀
extended meaning: Iwin basically refers to spirits which dwell on land, usually in thick forests. However, they do make themselves visible to people like hunters, herbalists, etc who have some supernatural powers. Sometimes, these people call on the services of these spirits to fight some deadly animals or other deadly spirits in times of danger. Iwíndàpọ̀ will, therefore, be a name that a hunter, or a herbalist who had survived a battle in some forest, or on a journey, or on an assignment with the help from spirits, will name their child.

name: Iwíndòkun
meaning: Iwin becomes (as mighty as) the ocean.

name: Iwínlọ́lá
meaning: 1. Iwin has riches. (Iwínlọ́lá) 2. Iwin is riches. (Iwinlọlá)

name: Iwínṣọlá
meaning: The spirit of the forest (a child of Ọbàtálá) gives honor/fame/elevation.

name: Iyìolúwadémiládé
meaning: The honour of God has crowned me (with the birth of my son).

name: Iyùnlọlá
meaning: This child of nobility is as precious as the iyùn ornament.

name: Iyìmikáyé
meaning: I am honoured around the world.

name: Ìbàdíàrán
meaning: One with buttocks for velvet clothing.

name: Ìbàjẹ́dẹwà
meaning: What was spoiled has turned to beauty.

name: Ìbìtẹ́yẹ
meaning: Being born give cause for celebration.

name: Ìbídòkun
meaning: Family has become large as the ocean.

name: Ìbídùnmóyè
meaning: Pedigree is good along with honour.

name: Ìbídọjà
extended meaning: What the name implies is that this birth has brought more attention to the family, as a market does.

name: Ìbídọlápọ̀
meaning: (Good) Birth has brought wealth from different avenues together.

name: Ìbígbèmí
meaning: 1. (Good) pedigree benefits me. 2. Family supports me.

name: Ìbílẹ́wà
meaning: Giving birth (or being given birth to) is good.

name: Ìbírọ̀gbàyímiká
meaning: (Good) birth surround me. Family surrounds me.

name: Ìbítáyọ̀
meaning: Giving birth is something to celebrate. Having a child brings joy.

name: Ìbítókun
meaning: Family is as large as the ocean.

name: Ìbítólú
meaning: To be born is enough to be called 'champion'.

name: Ìbítówa
meaning: Good pedigree is enough for us. [verification needed]

name: Ìbíwùmmí
meaning: Birth is desirable to me/ I wish for birth.

name: Ìbíwùnmí
meaning: I'm desirous of birth, birthing. Good birth is attractive to me.

name: Ìbídàpọ
extended meaning: "This is a name originating from people born through incestuous backgrounds. E.g. cousins, blood, or step, or half brothers or sisters etc" or "A child born to parents genealogically related (distant cousins)" - User feedback

name: Ìbítóyè
meaning: 1. Birth is worth chieftaincy. 2. The birth that survives.

name: Ìbùkún
extended meaning:
Literally, the name means "An addition"

"Ìbùkún" is a common abridged version of Ìbùkúnolúwa, Ìbùkúnadé, Ìbùkúnolú, etc.

name: Ìbùkúnolúwáyímiká
meaning: I am surrounded by God's blessing.

name: Ìbúkúnolúwápọ̀
meaning: The blessings of the lord is overwhelming.

name: Ìbírìndé
meaning: The birth brought back an ancestor.

name: Ìbírìnádé
meaning: Circumstances of the birth (of the child) led to royal (honors).

name: Ìbírónkẹ́
meaning: Family has found one to pamper.

name: Ìbírọ̀gbà
meaning: This birth had plenty family support.

name: Ìbẹ̀rẹ̀ọláayọ̀mi
meaning: The start of my joyous riches.

name: Ìdògbé
meaning: The third child born after a set of twins.
extended meaning: Also, the fifth child in a quintuplet.

name: Ìdòwú
meaning: A child born after a set of twins.

name: Ìféolúwátomi
meaning: The love of God is sufficient for me.

name: Ìfẹlànwá
meaning: Love it is that we're looking for.

name: Ìfẹ́dé
meaning: L amour est là. Love is here.

name: Ìfẹ́dẹ̀rù
meaning: Love becomes something to be awed by.

name: Ìfẹ́olúwanióṣẹ
meaning: The will of God was made manifest.

name: Ìfẹ́olúwapọ̀sími
meaning: The love of God is in abundant to me.

name: Ìfẹ́olúwa
meaning: 1. The love of God. 2. God's will.

name: Ìfẹ́túnwaṣe
meaning: Love repaired us. Love improved us. Love made us better.

name: Ìfẹ́táyọ̀
meaning: Love is as worthy as happiness.

name: Ìfẹ́tọ́lá
meaning: Being loved is a honour. Love is precious. Love is glorious.

name: Ìgbàgbọ́dayọ̀
extended meaning: The root "Ìgbàgbọ́" is also, more prominently, read as "Christianity" since it's a religion based on faith. So, we can also read it as "Christianity becomes joy."

name: Ìgbàgbọ́ládùn
extended meaning: The root "Ìgbàgbọ́" is also, more prominently, read as "Christianity" since it's a religion based on faith. So, we can also read it as "Christianity has sweetness."

name: Ìgbàgbọ́lékè
extended meaning: The root "Ìgbàgbọ́" is also, more prominently, read as "Christianity" since it's a religion based on faith. So, we can also read it as "Christianity triumphed."

name: Ìgbàgbọ́sanmí
extended meaning: The root "Ìgbàgbọ́" is also, more prominently, read as "Christianity" since it's a religion based on faith. So, we can also read it as "Christianity pays me."

name: Ìgbàgbọ́yẹmí
extended meaning: The root "Ìgbàgbọ́" is also, more prominently, read as "Christianity" since it's a religion based on faith. So, we can also read it as "Christianity befits me."

name: Ìgbàyílọlá
meaning: Now is the time for success/renown/wealth/honour.

name: Ìgbàyísanmí
meaning: This season is good for me.

name: Ìgbálájọbí
meaning: A child born (and cared for) by the whole world.

name: Ìgbìnkéke
meaning: A young member of the Ọbàtálá family.
extended meaning: This is an Ọbàtálá initiation name. The ìgbìn refers to the drum used by the worshipers of Ọbàtálá.
gloss: [{'ìgbìn': ' - the drum used by Ọbàtálá worshippers'}]

name: Ìjàdáhùn
extended meaning:
User comment:

"It originated from the Yorùbá god of local hunter (ode), meaning the god of hunting has answered prayers. It is a common name among various local hunter communities/gathering across the Yorùbá land.

name: Ìjàdópin
extended meaning: A name given to a child born after a major reconciliation either of the parents or of families.

name: Ìjàgbùlú
meaning: The town is filled with rancour.

name: Ìjàlànà
meaning: Quarrel opened the path (for this child).

name: Ìjàtúyì
meaning: The Ìjá divinity is worth value. [verification needed]

name: Ìjálúsì
meaning: The worship of the Ìjá divinity has become prosperous.

name: Ìjíwọlá
meaning: 1. The wind watches over (our) success. 2. The wind enters (our) wealth/success. [Verification needed]

name: Ìjòyè
meaning: 1. Chief 2. The act of becoming a chief
extended meaning: Given to a child born soon after the father (or the mother) received a chieftaincy title.

name: Ìkẹ́adé
meaning: The care of royalty. The one that royalty cares for/cherishes.

name: Ìkẹ́olú
meaning: A shortened form of Ìkẹ́olúwa: The care of God.

name: Ìlarí
meaning: This is a name given to a member of the king group of servants mostly in Ọ̀yọ́.
extended meaning: "Among the Lukumí in Cuba, this name has been retained. Its significance is understood to mean "King's (Shangó's) Messenger." It surely plays on the theme of the Ọ̀yọ́ palace Ìlàrís. It is accentuated according to Spanish grammatical dictates, as were all names in Cuba, as 'Ilarí Obá.'"

name: Ìlérí
extended meaning: Ìlérí can also be extended as Ìléríayọ̀, meaning 'promise of joy.'

name: Ìlúpéjú
meaning: The (important) faces of the town are complete. The town is now gathered.

name: Ìlútànmí
gloss: [{'ìlú': ' - town, the people of the town'}]

name: Ìlúyọ̀mádé
meaning: The town rejoices with the crown.

name: Ìlọ̀rí
meaning: A child who's mother got pregnant during a time when she is not menstruating.

name: Ìmọ́dòye
extended meaning: History: First encountered in D.O Fágúnwà's novel,  "Ògbójú Ọdẹ Nínú Igbó Irúnmọlẹ̀."

name: Ìníolúwa
meaning: The property of the lord. God's heritage.

name: Ìpínlayé
meaning: The world is filled with different destiny.

name: Ìrètíolúwa
meaning: God's hope. The expectation of God.

name: Ìrìnoyè
extended meaning: Name given to a child born during coronation, or on the day of the conferment of a chieftaincy title.

name: Ìshọ̀lá
extended meaning: The name is a cognomen, oríkì.

name: Ìtíọlá
gloss: [{'ìtí': ' - a collection of, a package of'}]

name: Ìtùnúọlá
meaning: The comfort that honour offers. The comfort that wealth offers.

name: Ìtẹ́gbọnà
meaning: The throne has space for artistry.

name: Ìtẹ́olúwakìsí
meaning: The throne of God cannot be moved.

name: Ìwàlẹ̀sìn
meaning: A good character is the core of religion. Religion is about character building.

name: Ìwájọmọ
meaning: Good character is better than having a child.

name: Ìwíladé
extended meaning: If you know the meaning of this name, please send it to via the "improve this entry" button.

name: Ìyanu
extended meaning: This is a modern Christian name given to a child born of extraordinary circumstances. A longer, more common form, is Ìyanuolúwa.

name: Ìyádùní
meaning: Mother is worth having. Mother is delightful to have.

name: Ìyámidé
meaning: My mother has returned, mother has come back.

name: Ìyániwúrà
extended meaning: A notable Yorùbá proverb says "Ìyá ni wúrà, baba ni jígí. Ọjọ́ ìyá kú ni wúrà bàjẹ́, ọjọ́ ti baba kú ni jígí wọmi."

name: Ìyániwúràọlá
meaning: Mother is the gold of nobility/success.

name: Ìyáṣàgbà
meaning: Motherhood is most prominent. Motherhood is king.

name: Ìyìnọlákàn
meaning: It's time for praise for (our) success.

name: Ìyàndá
meaning: A selected being. Specially or purposefully made.

name: Ìyádùnní
extended meaning: Also sometimes written as "Ìyádùní" or Ìyádùn-ń-ní.

name: Ìṣáfiádé
meaning: The Òrìṣå added royalty to us.

name: Jámíù
extended meaning: This is Yorúbá's version of the Arabic name "Jami'i or Jami'ah"

name: Jámọ́dù
meaning: My struggle is for the child. (Ìjà ọmọ ni mo dù)

name: Jákàndè
meaning: (One who) frees the sacrificial animal for the babaláwo.

name: Jésùfọlábòmí
meaning: Jesus covers me in success, notability.
extended meaning: This is a made-up Christian name. See also: Fọlábòmí.

name: Jésùpémi
extended meaning: Clearly a Christian name, and most likely a recent adaptation of earlier names like Ọ̀súnpémi, Ifápémi, etc.

name: Jésùtómigbà
meaning: Jesus is enough to save me.

name: Jéyifó
meaning: Let this one float (on the surface).

name: Jimoh
meaning: Yoruba's version of the Arabic name Al-Jumu'ah which means 'the congregation'
extended meaning: Because of the use of this name to denote Friday, when muslims typically congregate to pray, this name has also been given to children born on a Friday.

name: Jìmí
extended meaning: Short form of Olújìnmi or Fọlájìnmí, etc. Check those entries for the full meaning.

name: Jìnmí
extended meaning: Short form of Olújìnmi, Fọlájìnmi, etc. See them for full meaning.

name: Jíbówú
extended meaning: This is a name given to children from welding or blacksmithing families.

name: Jíbódù
meaning: Wakes up to the Ifá corpus.

name: Jógunómí
extended meaning: This is the name of a famous Yorùbá warrior.

name: Jókòtadé
meaning: Wait with the crown. Sit with the crown/royalty.

name: Jókòtìmí
extended meaning: It is a name given to perceived àbíkú children asking them to stop dying.

name: Jólẹ̀dó
meaning: Let the owner of the land dwell in it. [verification needed]

name: Jùmọbí
extended meaning: Usually written in full with a prefix of Adé, Olú, or Ọlá.

name: Jùmọ̀kẹ́
extended meaning: This is a common short form of a longer name. See "variants".

name: Jùwọ́n
meaning: More than them/Bigger than them. Olúwajùwọ́n: God is more than/ above them. Ọlájùwọ́n: Nobility/wealth is more than them.

name: Jésùtófúnmi
extended meaning: This is a modern Christian variation of Olútófúnmi, Adétófúnmi, etc.

name: Jésùtósin
extended meaning: This is a Christian adaptation of "Olútósìn"

name: Jímiwò
extended meaning: A full name like Adéjímiwò will mean "Royalty woke up to stare at me", where the 'jí' would have changed meaning to become 'wake up' or 'arise'.

name: Jẹ́aríọgbé
extended meaning: This is a typical àbíkú name, given to a child as a way to entreat him/her to stay after many deaths.

name: Jẹ́misìgbìn
extended meaning: The ìgbìn is a type of drum used by the worshipers of Ọbàtálá.

name: Jẹ́njẹ̀
meaning: Let me rest. Let me eat. Let me enjoy.

name: Jẹ́nrẹ́yìn
meaning: Allow me to see my future.

name: Jọba
extended meaning: Short form of a longer name: Olújọba, Adéjọba, etc

name: Jọláolú
meaning: One who benefits from the wealth of the lord.

name: Jọláolúwa
meaning: Enjoy the wealth of the lord. Enjoy the benefit of God.

name: Jọláorími
meaning: Enjoy the benefit of my creator.

name: Jọláoshó
meaning: Enjoy the riches of a sorcerer.

name: Jọláadé
meaning: (One who) Enjoys the goodness of royalty.

name: Jọládèmí
meaning: Enjoys wealth before I get back.

name: Jọláóyẹmí
meaning: Let wealth be worthy of me.

name: Jọ́láyẹmí
meaning: Let wealth be worthy of me.

name: Kakaǹfò
meaning: The title of the Yorùbá generalissimo.

name: Kalẹ̀jayé
extended meaning: This is an abikú name, given to children born after many trials.

name: Karóunwí
meaning: Another way of writing "Károhunwí": That we may find something to say.

name: Kàsálí
meaning: Yorúbá's version of the Arabic name "Al-Ghazali".
extended meaning: Taken from the name of a Muslim theologian, jurist, philosopher, and mystic of Persian descent, Abū Ḥāmid Muḥammad ibn Muḥammad al-Ghazālī. He is from Ghazali somewhere in the present day Iran.

name: Kàsímù
meaning: Yoruba's version of the Arabic name 'Qasim' which means 'handsome and generous'
extended meaning: It was the name of one of the sons of the Prophet of Islam, Muhammad

name: Kádijú
meaning: Let's close our eyes (and pretend to die, just to see who will mourn one).
extended meaning:
It is my belief that the name comes from a proverb. The full would be “Kádijú, ká láa kú, ká wo ẹni tí yóó sunkún ẹni, ká bùrìn, bùrìn, ká f'ẹsẹ̀ kọ, ká wo ẹni tí yóó ṣeni pẹ̀lẹ́“  

My dad recently sent this translation “Ká-di- ojú (close your eyes), ká pé a kú ( pretend that you are dead), ká wo ẹni tí yóó sunkún ẹni (imagine who would mourn one)" And we are from Ìsẹ́yìn.

- User explanation.

name: Kájọpáíyé
meaning: Together, we shall stay/tarry long in the world. Together, we shall live long.

name: Kájọpẹ́láyéọlá
meaning: Together, let's stay together in the world on wealth.

name: Kálènìkànṣe
meaning: ..that we can do it alone/by oneself.

name: Kálẹ́yẹmíjòwúrọ̀lọ
meaning: May my latter days be more favourable than early years.

name: Kányinsọ́lá
meaning: Make wealth have more savour. Add a taste of sweetness to wealth.

name: Kányìnọlá
meaning: The last (or the zenith) of wealth.
gloss: [{'kẹ́yìn': ' - reach the ultimate, be the last'}]

name: Káróhunwí
meaning: So we can have something to say.

name: Kásìmawò
extended meaning: The tonal variation on the last vowel insists that we write it as "Kásìmawòó". It is an àbíkú-themed name for children not usually expected to grow into adulthood.

name: Káṣìmáawòó
extended meaning: This is an àbíkú name, given to a child believed to be prone to dying only to return again in the future.

name: Kádírì
meaning: Yorúbá's version of the Arabic name "Abdul Qadir" meaning servant of the Able One.
extended meaning: It is taken from one of the 100 names of Allah.

name: Káshìmawò
extended meaning: This is a common spelling of an abíkú name "Káṣìmáawòó".

name: Káyọ̀dé
meaning: Brings lots of happiness with him/her.

name: Kekú
extended meaning: The full saying is "Kekúlọ́mọdé, àgbà ló ń dà."

name: Kéwúlabí
meaning: We've given birth to the Qu'ran.

name: Kìítán
extended meaning:
The name is often preceded by common roots like Ọlá, Adé, Oyè, etc. 

This is a common short form of Ọlákìítán.

name: Kìkìirelolúwa
meaning: God is pure goodness. God is all good.

name: Kìkìolúwa

name: Kìkìọláolúwa

gloss: [{'kìkì': ' - only, filled with, just and only'}]

name: Kíkẹ́lọmọ
meaning: The child is for petting/caring for.

name: Kílànkó

name: Kòbọmọjẹ́
meaning: He hasn't spoilt the essence of the child. i.e. He/she is respectable.

name: Kòfowórayọ̀
meaning: He/she didn't use money to buy happiness.

name: Kòfowórọlá

name: Kòníbàjẹ́

name: Kòníbirè

name: Kòséfowórà

name: Kòsọ́mọlátẹ

name: Kòtóyẹ́
meaning: It's important to be focused. [verification needed]

name: Kórebiọba
meaning: To bring forth goodness like a king

name: Kóyinsọ́lá
meaning: Add honey into wealth. Add sweetness into success.
extended meaning: The name is often mispronunced as Kányinsọ́lá and may have been given intended actually as that, and then misspelt. Kóyinsọ́lá is not very commonly given/borne. For the common name, see Kányinsọ́lá or Kọ́nyinsọ́lá

name: Kúdáyìsí
extended meaning: This is a common written form of Ikúdáyìsí.

name: Kúdírátù
extended meaning:
User feedback:
Kúdírátù is the Yorùbá pronounciation of the Arabic word Qudrah. This is a common Muslim name. To say "Insha Allah bi qudratullah" in Arabic means "By Allah's power".

name: Kújọọ́rẹ̀

extended meaning: An àbíkú name. See also: Kújọwọ́rẹ̀.

name: Kúmápàyí
extended meaning: This name is given to a child in the olden days to prevent a child from dying if the mother had had previous child dying (Abiku). The full name is Kíkúmápàyí - death should not kill this.

name: Kúmolúyì
meaning: Death knows the one who is honourable/affluent.

name: Kúnbi
meaning: A shortened form of "Adékúnbi": Adds to birth. [verification needed]

name: Kúnlé
extended meaning: This is a usual short form of Adékúnlé, Olúkúnlé, etc

name: Kúnrunmí
extended meaning: This is another spelling of Kúrunmí.

name: Kúpọlátì
meaning: Death has been unable to destroy nobility/dignity.

name: Kúrúyẹjó
meaning: One short but graceful on the dance floor.
extended meaning: A nickname/cognomen given to a short person.

name: Kúṣànú
extended meaning: Though the name is typically written as Kúṣànú, the best phonological representation should be Kúṣàánú.

name: Kúpolúyi
meaning: Death has killed the honoured one.
extended meaning: The name could also be a prayer: Kí ikú má pa olúyì: death shouldn't kill the honored one.

name: Kájọpáyé
meaning: Together, we shall stay/tarry long in the world. Together, we shall live long.

name: Kìkìọpẹ́
meaning: Just gratitude (is what is deserving of God).

name: Kíyèsẹ́ní
extended meaning: This is a name given to a child whose size at the early stages is very small. The name is a reference to others walking by the mat to be careful not to step on the baby because of its size.
gloss: [{'kiyèsí': ' - be aware of, be careful about, pay attention to'}]

name: Kònáyọ̀
extended meaning: An abíkú name from Benin Republic (Ketu/Ketou)

name: Kòṣééfọ́wọ́kàn

name: Kúmólú

name: Kúpàyí
meaning: Death did not killed this one.

name: Kẹjọọlá

name: Kẹ́mi

name: Kẹ́hìndé

name: Kọ̀gbẹ̀

An àbíkú name.

name: Kọ́lédowó

name: Kọ́lédoyè

name: Kọ́lédọlá

name: Layọ̀mi

name: Làlà
extended meaning: "A nickname among the warriors of Olúkòyí lineage."

name: Làsísì
meaning: The Yorùbá version of Abdulazeez, an Arabic name.

name: Làtífù
extended meaning: This is a Yorùbá version of an Arabic name, AbdelLateef.

name: Lábísí
extended meaning: This is a common short form of Ọlábísí.

name: Ládélé
meaning: A short form of "Ọládélé": Wealth/nobility has arrived at home.

name: Ládìtàn
meaning: The wealth has become generational. (A variant of Ọládìtàn)

name: Ládípọ̀

name: Ládòkun
meaning: Wealth becomes the ocean. [Shortened form of "Ọládòkun"]

name: Láìtán
meaning: A shortened form of Ọláìítán: wealth never finishes.

name: Láí
meaning: Short form of Láyíwọlá, Láyí, Láíwọlá

name: Láídé

name: Lákòńdórò

name: Lálùdé
meaning: The noble one entered to drumming/celebration.

name: Lámíkanra
extended meaning: "The story I was told about the name was that two families decided to come together to become one family and the root name is ọlá méjì mí kan ara: two families have joined together to become one." - User feedback.

name: Lánre
meaning: Short for Ọlánrewájú: Wealth/nobility is progressing.

name: Láoyè
meaning: A variant of "Ọláoyè": the wealth of honour.

name: Lásún
extended meaning: A shortened form of Ọlásúnmádé or Ọlásúnkànmí

name: Lásúnmádé
meaning: Wealth moves closer to the crown.

name: Látọ̀nà
meaning: 1. Nobility knows the way. 2. Nobility is right.

name: Láwóore
meaning: A short form of Ọláwóore: Wealth seeks goodness.

name: Ládi
meaning: A shortened form of "Oladipúpọ" or "Ọládiméjì" or "Ládiípọ̀"

name: Lásebìkan
meaning: Ọláṣebìkan: Wealth doesn't belong in one place.

name: Lékan
meaning: Full name: Ọlálékan/Ọlámilékan - My wealth has been added upon.

name: Lékè
extended meaning: Shortened form of Olúwalékè, Gbémilékè, Adélékè...

name: Lékútì
meaning: The house has refused to die.

name: Lógunléko
meaning: 1. A warrior in Lagos 2. A strong, warlike, or rascally person.
extended meaning:
"Lógunléko derives from Ológunkúteré, one of the former kings of Lagos. His real name was Kúteré, but because he was a very warlike personality, they added the name Ológun to his name and he became known thenceforth as Ológunkúteré. 

Because he was from Lagos and he lived in Lagos, he became known as Ológun Lékòó or Lóogunléko, which means "the Warlike one of Lagos" . 

Since then any warlike person or any particularly rascally person is often referred to as Lóogunléko, after the original Ológun Lékòó, Ológunkúteré, the warlike one of Lagos."

History by Daniel Ayọ̀délé Adéníran on Facebook (https://www.facebook.com/kolatubosun/posts/10156368187549235?comment_id=10156368279529235&reply_comment_id=10156368363504235&comment_tracking=%7B"tn"%3A"R6"%7D)

name: Lúbọ́rọ̀jí
gloss: [{'olú': ' - prominent one, star child, chief, head'}]

name: Lúfadéjù
meaning: The slave, because of a crown, is greater.

name: Láyọkùn
extended meaning:
Literally: Wealth grew a fat belly.
The “wealth” referring to as “ọlá” is actually not just about affluence growing (a belly). Because here the “ọlá” is being given a subject role in which it is forced to be more than wealth or nobility – that it actually becomes a person! Thus that “wealth” referring to “ọlá” in Láyọkùn, is more about: human potential, largeness of heart, generosity of spirit (and of materials, yes), nobility, dignity, and grace becoming bigger.

name: Lóbìdé
gloss: [{'olóbí': ' - the kolanut seller, the owner of the kolanut'}]

name: Lẹshi
extended meaning: Derived from Ẹ̀gbá phrase referring to a horde or body of people or in describing the wave of attack of the Dahomey in their campaign against Ẹ̀gbá. Usage example: Lẹshi-lẹshi ni wọn wá

name: Mayùngbẹ́
meaning: Do not crave the woods (burial place).

name: Màmátóókí
meaning: Mother is worthy to be praised.

name: Mábínúọlámi
meaning: Don't be envious of my nobility.

name: Mábòlóṣìrìn
meaning: Do not walk with the wretched.
extended meaning: It's important to point out that as snobbish as the name sounds when seen through the lens of a well-to-do person swearing off the company of the poor, there might be another way to look at it if olòṣì is read more as a ne'er-do-well rather than just a a poor one.

name: Mábọ̀gájẹ́
meaning: 1. Do not ridicule the boss. 2. Do not damage your leadership role.

name: Májẹ́kódùnmí
extended meaning: A general consensus is that this name is given to a child born after some other misfortune, be it the death of a previous child or any other major catastrophe - as a supplication to the creator to prevent a repeat.

name: Májọ́lágbé
meaning: Don't let nobility/success go to waste.

name: Málọmọ́
extended meaning: This is a name for perceived àbíkú children, urging them to stay back.

name: Mánàárẹ
meaning: Why don't you believe in yourself (and not say you have others on whom to depend)?
extended meaning: "The name, Mánáarẹ--a poor approximation that elides the complex tone glides to which the Roman alphabet is deaf--cannot but catch my attention because it recalls childhood memories of striking characters so named in Imuṣin, the Ìjẹ̀bú town in which I was raised, and also because it is not in standard, Ọ̀yọ́ centered, dialect of written Yorùbà. In Ìjẹ̀bú dialect, the brave hunter's name is a shortened form of a longer admonition to those who are unnecessarily exuberant about (or reliant upon) social connections, "mánáárẹ, kó fọ́ wo nọ́ni." The poetry of the sentence follows an ironic formulation. We can interpret it roughly as "shouldn't you claim your own self first before boasting of your access to others." Of course, it could also be used to put down a boisterous rival." - Professor Adelékè Adéẹ̀kọ́

name: Mánárẹ
extended meaning: "The name, Mánáarẹ--a poor approximation that elides the complex tone glides to which the Roman alphabet is deaf--cannot but catch my attention because it recalls childhood memories of striking characters so named in Imuṣin, the Ìjẹ̀bú town in which I was raised, and also because it is not in standard, Ọ̀yọ́ centered, dialect of written Yorùbà. In Ìjẹ̀bú dialect, the brave hunter's name is a shortened form of a longer admonition to those who are unnecessarily exuberant about (or reliant upon) social connections, "mánáarẹ, kó í fọ wò nọ́ni." The poetry of the sentence follows an ironic formulation. We can interpret it roughly as "shouldn't you claim your own self first before boasting of your access to others." Of course, it could also be used to put down a boisterous rival." - Professor Adelékè Adéẹ̀kọ́

name: Mápàyí
extended meaning: The name is a prayer, pleading that the gods not kill the child as they have done with earlier ones. This is a name given, usually to suspected àbíkú children.

name: Mápowórọlá
meaning: Don't spend hard earned money chasing honour to buy.

name: Máràiyésá
meaning: Do not run from the world.

name: Máràyésa
meaning: Do not run from the world.

name: Máránróọlá
meaning: Do not avenge the hurt of wealth.

name: Máwobẹ̀
meaning: Ignore that. Don't pay attention to it.

name: Máyaléèké
meaning: Don't visit the house of the dishonest person.

name: Májàsán
meaning: He who does not eat tasteless food.

name: Mákànjúore
meaning: Don't be too much in a hurry for good.

name: Mákànjúọlá
meaning: Don't be too much in a hurry for wealth.

name: Málàólú
meaning: He who brings white emblem to the deity (Ọbàtálá)

name: Mébáwọndù
meaning: I did not struggle with them.

name: Médùnà
gloss: [{'mé': ' - I am not, I do not'}]

name: Méjińdé
meaning: One born during the rain or raining season.

name: Méròyá
meaning: I couldn't find money to borrow.

name: Méròyí
extended meaning: The name expresses surprise either at the gender of the child or at the arrival of the child at all, perhaps due to a pervasive childlessness.

name: Mobíìná
meaning: I've given birth to this already.

name: Mobíyìná
meaning: I've given birth to this already.

name: Mobólúrìn
meaning: I walk with God. I walk with the prominent one.

name: Mobísọ́lá
extended meaning: "Given to me by my grandfather (or so I heard) who is from a place called Ijomu-Oro (one of the towns under the Oro kingdom) in Kwara state."

name: Mobọ́ládalẹ́
meaning: I've taken wealth/luxury into my old age. [See below for extra information about the name.]
extended meaning: A name given to a child born by relatively old parents, particularly the father who is still doing well in business, wealth and prosperity.

name: Mobọ́lọ́mọpé
meaning: I'm now at one with those who have children. I've left the group of the childless.

name: Modádéayọ̀
meaning: I wear the crown of joy.

name: Modébádé
meaning: I have arrived into royalty / I have arrived to meet the crown.

name: Modébáyọ̀
meaning: I have arrived into joy. I have arrived to meet joy.

name: Modébọ́lá
meaning: I arrived to meet wealth already there.

name: Modébọ́lánlé
meaning: I arrived at home to meet wealth already there.

name: Modésífẹ́olúwa
meaning: I have come into god's love.

name: Modésíreolúwa
meaning: I have entered into the lord's goodness.

name: Modúpẹ́adé
meaning: I am thankful for the crown.

name: Mofaratireolúwami
meaning: I'm resting on the goodness of my God.

name: Mofèyíṣará
meaning: I use this (child) as a family.

name: Mofèyíṣaráminílúaláìlárá

extended meaning: Never having found anywhere else online or offline where this name is borne in the full form, we'd assume that it was made up, though the sentiment that it conveys is one very common among the Yorùbá: that of a parent in a new town or city with only a new child as company or comfort, perhaps because of the absence of the child's father, or any other equally alienating circumstance.

name: Mofìhìnfólúwa
meaning: I give praises to the lord.

name: Mofìhìnsólúwa
meaning: I give praises to the lord.

name: Mofìyìnfólúwa
meaning: I give praises to the lord.

name: Mofìyìnsólúwa
meaning: I give praises to the lord.

name: Mofiọláolúwamí
meaning: 1. I breathe with the success/wealth of God. 2. I breathe with the grace of God.

name: Mofolúshọ́
meaning: I've granted to God for safekeeping.

name: Mofolúṣọ́
meaning: I grant to God for protection.

name: Mofólúwawò
meaning: I've given (him/her) to God to care for.

name: Mofólúwaṣọ́

name: Mofẹláolúwa

name: Mofẹ́olúwa

name: Mofẹ́tolúwa

name: Mofọ́lọ́runsọ́
meaning: I give to the lord to watch over.

name: Mogbójúrí

name: Mogbárímú

name: Mogbọ́júnádé

name: Mojí

name: Mojírọ́lá

name: Mojírólúwa

name: Mojoyinolúwa
meaning: I enjoy the sweetness of God.

name: Mojoyinọlá

name: Mojúbàolú

name: Mojọláolú

name: Mojọláolúwa
meaning: 1. I enjoy the affluence of God. 2. I benefit from the influence of God.
extended meaning:
In Yorùbá, ọlá can mean "affluence", but it can also mean "the benefit of..." as in the name Ọláìyá (the benefit of mother). When people say 'Ọlá XYZ ni mo jẹ' it means a person has benefited positively from the influence of another. Many times when this is invoked, an unpleasant outcome is averted simply because of the goodwill and social capital of another.
Read more: http://blog.yorubaname.com/2016/12/12/ola-isnt-always-wealth/

name: Mokọ́ládé
meaning: I have brought wealth, influence, affluence.

name: Moláyọ̀
meaning: I have joy. I am well indulged.

name: Momoreolúwa
meaning: I know the goodness of the lord.

name: Momọoreolúwa

name: Monínínúọlá

name: Moráláyọ̀
meaning: I see a joyful person. I've seen the bearer of joy.

name: Morádékẹ́

name: Morádéwún

name: Morádéyọ̀

See also: Morádéhún, Morádéwún.
See also: Arádéyọ̀

name: Morìnádé
meaning: ==homograph== 1. I walk to have royalty. 2. I walk into royalty.

name: Morífẹolúwa
meaning: I see the love of God.

name: Morífẹ̀ẹ́

A better phonetic representation of the tones would have the name as Moríìfẹ́.

See also: Moráyọ, Moríre, Morádé

name: Moríreayọ̀
meaning: I have seen the goodness of joy.

name: Moróhunmúbọ̀

name: Morótì

meaning: I've found something to give to God.

name: Moróhunfólúwa
meaning: I have found something to give to the lord.

name: Moróundíyà

name: Moríreolúwa
meaning: I have seen the goodness of God

name: Moróhunfọ́lá

name: Morẹ́nikéjì

name: Morẹ́nikẹ́

name: Morọ́láolúwa

name: Morọ́lápé

name: Morọ́láyọ̀

name: Morọ́lákẹ́

name: Morọ́láún

name: Morọ́mọkẹ́

name: Morọ́pẹ́dá

name: Morọ́lábí
meaning: I have found wealth to birth.

name: Mosádomi

name: Moshọpẹfólúwa
meaning: I am grateful for the lord.

name: Mosúnmóluwa
meaning: I move closer to the Lord

name: Mosúnmọ́lá
meaning: I have moved close to nobility.

name: Mosọpẹolúwa
meaning: I gave the thanks of the lord.

name: Mosọpẹ́fólúwa
meaning: I gave thanks to the Lord.

name: Motiaraolúwajáde
meaning: I am formed out of God’s body.

name: Motirọ́láolúwa
meaning: I have seen the wealth of God.

name: Motórọ́lá
meaning: I'm old/big/mature enough to see/find wealth/success.

name: Motúnrádé
meaning: I have seen another royal one.

name: Motúnráyọ̀

name: Motúnrọ́lákẹ́
meaning: I've found wealth (in this child) to care for again.

name: Motúnyọ̀sólúwa

name: Motẹ́rígbareolúwa

name: Motọ́lání
meaning: I'm great enough to have wealth.

name: Motọ́lágbé
meaning: I'm big enough to carry wealth.

name: Mowátẹ́ní

name: Mowátẹ́níayọ̀
meaning: I've come to spread the mat of joy.

name: Moyọ̀

Shortened form of:

Moyọ̀sóreolúwa
Moyọ̀fólú
Moyọ̀sádé
Moyọ̀sọ́lá

meaning: I rejoice in the king of glory.

name: Moyọ̀síreolúwa

name: Moyọ̀sọ́sun

name: Mòńrẹ́nikéjì

name: Mórìn
meaning: This can be one of: 1. "Morìn" as in Morìnsọ́lá (I walk into wealth) 2. "Mọ́rìn" as in Ọmọ́rìnsọ́lá (The child walks into wealth)

name: Mórítìwọ̀n
meaning: I have seen their... (their problems, success, lifestyle)

name: Moṣaléwá
meaning: I have been choosy about which house to get into.

name: Moṣerere
meaning: I do well and I prosper.

name: Moṣọbalájé
meaning: I become the king of resourcefulness.

name: Moṣọpẹsólúwa
meaning: I give thanks to the lord.

name: Múdélé
extended meaning: Likely given to a child born abroad.

name: Múléró
meaning: Uphold the family. The one who upholds the family. Shortened form of Òpómúléró.

name: Múráínọ̀
meaning: Imran (father of Maryam in the Qur'an)
extended meaning: Adaptation into Yoruba of an Arabic name.

name: Múyìnfọ́lá
meaning: Respect wealth. Give honour to nobility. Be thankful for grace.

name: Múyìwá
meaning: 1. Brought this. [A shortened form of "Olúmúyìíwá"] 2. Brought honour [A shortened form of "Olúmúyìwá"]
extended meaning: The name is usually preceded by any of Yorùbá's prominent root morphemes: "olú" or "adé" or "oyè", etc.

name: Máfowórọlá
meaning: An honour not bought with money.

name: Máfọláyọ̀mí
meaning: Do not mock me with (your) success.

name: Mágbaraléwọn
meaning: Do not rely on them. Do not trust them.

name: Májẹ̀ódùnmí
meaning: Let me not be in pain.

name: Mẹ́bùdé
meaning: Come to me with gifts. Meet me with gifts.

name: Mọmíjí
extended meaning: "My father was in a car accident and went into a coma when I was born. But he woke up a week after I was born and that’s how my mother named me, according to my dad. Unfortunately, my mother died when I was 6 and I’m not in touch with anyone on my mother’s side, but she was from Ibadan. I’ve never been able to find this meaning for my name online so through my own research, I’m assuming she made it up with ọmọ, mí, and jí."

name: Mọrèmi
meaning: The child is attractive to me.

name: Mọ́lákẹ́
meaning: A child of nobility to care for.

name: Mọ́reni
meaning: 1. The child is desirable to me. (Mọ́reni) 2. I've found a person (Morẹ́ni)
extended meaning:
Mọ́reni is another version of Mọ́remí
Morẹ́ni is a shortened form of Morẹ́nikẹ́

name: Mọ́rìnsọ́lá
meaning: 1. Mọ́rìnsọ́lá: The child walks into wealth/nobility. 2. Morìnsọ́lá: I walk into wealth/nobility.

name: Mọ́ríléwá
meaning: Abridged form of Ọmọ́ríléwá: The child has found a home to come to.

name: Mọ́ríyebá
meaning: The child has (many) women at his/her back.
extended meaning:
This is a name given to a child whose birth was surrounded by trials. The name implies a relief that the mother made it through the travails enough to meet the child.

It can also be for a child whose mother died shortly after he/she is born.

name: Mọ́tiléwá
meaning: One who comes from a (good) home.

name: Mọ́yẹni
meaning: The child is worthy of one.

name: Níètí
extended meaning: A Ketou name from Benin Republic.

name: Nífiṣe
extended meaning: From Matthew 21: 3: Olúwanífiṣe: "And if any man say ought unto you, ye shall say, The Lord hath need of them; and straightway he will send them."

name: Níkẹ
meaning: Adorable, cherished. Short form of Adéníkẹ́, Olúníkẹ́, Ọláníkẹ́, etc

name: Níníọlá
extended meaning: The full sentence is "Níníọlá ò kan agbára", meaning "having wealth is not by your strength."

name: Ochún ladé
extended meaning: Lukumi name from Cuba, a version of Ọ̀ṣunladé. See also: Ochun Ladde

name: Ochún miguá
meaning: For practitioners of Cuban òrìs̩à tradition, which is the Yorùbá-based religious tradition that developed in Cuba, Ochún Miguá is said to mean "Oshún (a Yorùbá river deity) brought this one in her arms." It is used within the Cuban òrìṣà community as a possible name for initiates of that goddess. The equivalent Yorùbá name in West Africa is "Ò̩s̩únmúyìíwá," which means "Ò̩s̩un (a Yorùbá river deity) brought this one."
extended meaning: Used in Cuba for initiated of the deity Oshún.  (rendered Ò̩s̩un in Yorùbáland of West Africa)

name: Ocán tomí
meaning: It is said among devotees within cuban òrìs̩à tradition that the name means "water and heart," or, alternately, "heart of water." In yoruba language, the name is derived from several possibilities. Ò̩kántò̩mí is the abbreviation of Ò̩kántò̩míwá or Ò̩kántò̩mídé, meaning "one (child) came directly to me" or "one (child) arrived directly to me." It can be used to refer to a child born after one has attended a festival for devotion to a yorùbá deity praying for assistance with fertility. Another possibility is Ò̩kántómi, meaning "one is enough for me." It suggests that the mother or parents gave birth to a single child after many failed attemps or infant deaths. (àbíkú)
extended meaning:
Ocán tomí is a popular name used among initiates of the deity Oshún (Ò̩s̩un in yorùbá language) within cuban orisa tradition known as Santería, Lucumí tradition, or Regla de Ocha. 

Chief Fama, in her book "Òrìs̩à Names", suggests that it is derived from the name "Ò̩s̩unnìkantóómi" meaning "only Ò̩s̩un is enough for me."

name: Oddualá
meaning: Among practitioners of Cuban Òrìsà tradition/remnants of Yorùbá culture in Cuba, the belief is that it means "the mantle of the prince." In fact, this is derived from the Yorùbá name "Odùo̩lá" which means "Odù of wealth." Depending on context, Odù may refer to Orisa Odù, the deity who is the principal wife of the Ọ̀rúnmìlà. But it is also a name given primarily to devotees and priests of Òrìṣà Odùduwà, ancestral father of the Yorùbá nation.
extended meaning: The name is used in Cuba as well as in countries of the cuban diaspora such as Venezuela, Panama, Puerto Rico, United States, Spain, Mexico, among others.  It is typically one of the possible names that can be given to initiates of O̩bàtálá in the Cuban orisa tradition.
gloss: [{'Odù': ' - abbreviated form in reference to the historic and religious figure Odùduwà, father of the Yoruba nation'}]

name: Oddufora
meaning: Among practitioners of Cuban Òrìṣà tradition known as Santería (Lucumí), the belief is that it means "the wandering prince." It is a name typically given to Ọbàtálá initiates in the Yorùbá-based religious tradition of Cuba.
extended meaning:
Oddufora is the spelling used among practitioners of cuban orisa tradition for the name. It is one of the names among cubans given to an initiate of the deity Obatala.

In Yorùbá language of southwestern Nigeria, the name "Odùúfowórà" is one associated with the deity Odùduwà. It is derived from "o̩mo̩ tí Odù (Odùduwà) fi owó rà,"  meaning "the child that Odùduwà purchased with money" (spent lavishly to obtain). It can also be spelled "Odùfoórà."

This name was brought to my attention by Antón Vélez of Havana, Cuba.
gloss: [{'Odù': ' - the deity Odùduwà, the Ifá corpus'}]

name: Odùbanjọ
meaning: The Ifá priesthood/corpus is in agreement with me.

name: Odùbàjò
meaning: The Odù head has returned from a journey.

name: Odùbádéjọ
meaning: The corpus is at one with the crown.

name: Odùbógun
meaning: The Ifá corpus met with war.

name: Odùbọ́nàjọ
meaning: The corpus is at one with art.

name: Odùfóyè
meaning: 1. Odù married honour. 2. Odù wants honour.

name: Odùjọbí
meaning: The Ifá corpus gave birth to (this) jointly.

name: Odùkálé
meaning: The Ifa corpus surrounds my home.
extended meaning: Another way to look at it would be "Ifá protects the home".

name: Odùlàjà
meaning: The Ifá corpus settled a fight.

name: Odùlàtẹ̀
extended meaning: Odùlàtẹ̀ is an Ijebu name, their ancestors lived between Ikorodu in today's Lagos state and Sagamu in Ogun state. It was the creation of Lagos state in 1967 that separated their home from their farmland. Some of their first generations settled at home ( Ikorodu) some settled in the farmland ( Sagamu)

name: Odùlé
meaning: The Odù is more than enough.

name: Odùmádé
meaning: The corpus has carried the crown.

name: Odùmákin
meaning: The Ifá corpus has picked, chosen, valor (the brave one).

name: Odùmbọ́ní
meaning: The Odù I have in my hands.

name: Odùtáyọ̀
meaning: Odù (Ifá) is worth being joyful about, is worth celebrating.

name: Odùtọ́lá
meaning: The Ifá corpus is enough for wealth.

name: Odùwọlé
meaning: The corpus has entered the house.

name: Odùwọ̀bi
meaning: The Odù has entered the family.

name: Odùṣọ̀tẹ̀
meaning: The Ifá corpus is not treacherous.

name: Odùlójú
meaning: The Ifá corpus has eyes (can see).

name: Odùmósùn
meaning: The Ifa corpus took (charge of) the Ifá staff.

name: Ofeicita
meaning: In cuban usage, the meaning they give it is "witness of the itá." (Itá is what cuban orisa devotees refer to the divination with 16 cowries shells on the 3rd day of an orisa initiation.) This name is derived from Fèyís̩ìtàn (alternately "Fèyís̩ètàn"), short for "Olúfèyís̩ètàn," meaning "The head of the household used this one to make memorable history."
extended meaning:
The name is used among those that practice afrocuban Òrìṣà religion. It is often used as a temporary or long-term title for one that is particularly good at transcribing the divinatory information given to the initiate of a cuban orisa initiation. In the same cuban orisa tradition, it can be chosen through the oracle to be the spiritual name of an orisa initiate. Cuban practitioners consider Òrìs̩à Ò̩s̩un to be the first transcriber of oracular information during òrìsà initiation and hence is the first "ofeicita." (witness of the life-reading for an initiate)

In Ò̩yó̩ dialect, Fèyís̩ìtàn is pronounced / rendered "Fèyísìtàn" WITHOUT the diacritic under the “s”.

name: Ogun yobí
extended meaning: This is a Lukumi name from Cuba, likely a corruption of Ògúnjọbí

name: Ogúnfùsìká

name: Ogúngbọlá

name: Ogúnnòìkí

name: Ogúnwùnmí
gloss: [{'ògún': ' - Ògún, the Yorùbá god of iron'}]

name: Ogúnlẹ́yẹ
gloss: [{'ògún': ' - Ògún, the Yorùbá god of iron'}]

name: Ogúnmodìmú

name: Ogúntókun

name: Ogúntómisìn
meaning: Ògún is enough for me to worship.

name: Ojóṣìpẹ̀
gloss: [{'òjọ́': ' - the child born with the umbilical cord on his neck'}]

name: Ojúbánirẹ́
meaning: One with pleasant demeanour in people's presence.

name: Ojúkòtọ́lá

name: Ojúlàárí

name: Ojúloge

meaning: The eyes of God are sufficient to watch over me.

name: Ojúòkáiyé
meaning: The eyes can't see all of the world.

name: Ojúróngbé

extended meaning: A clearer interpretation of the name would be that the child is pretty enough on the eyes. The eyes (of the beholder) has achieved prominence by being able to find this (child).

name: Ojúróungbé
meaning: The eyes has seen something worth carrying.

name: Ojútikú
meaning: Death has been put to shame.

name: Ojúọba
meaning: The eyes (or representatives) of the king.

name: Ojúọlápé
meaning: The faces of wealth are complete. Everyone who is important is now here.
extended meaning:
User feedback: 

"My parents gave me this name in honor of my paternal grandmother. My dad is her youngest and I am his oldest. I was that completion of faces that brought wealth to my grandma's old age I guess."

name: Ojúmitúnráyọ̀
meaning: My eyes have seen joy again.

name: Ojútaláyọ̀
extended meaning: This name is typically given to a child born either after a long wait, or after a major embarrassing event in the family.

name: Okàntómi
meaning: This is a name given after ordination of an Orisha priest/ess in the Afro-Cuban Yoruba religious tradition known as Lukumi/Santeria/Regla de Ocha. This particular name is given to Oshun worshipers, and believed to mean something like "Oshun's Heart" "Heart of Water" "Heart that is water" or even "Oshun is sufficient".

name: Okédòkun
meaning: The mountain has become an ocean.

name: Okùbánjọ

extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.

name: Okùbóyèjọ
meaning: The god of wealth is at one with honour.
extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.

name: Okùnúgà
meaning: The god of enterprise reigns supreme.
extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.

name: Okùnẹ́yẹ

extended meaning: Okù derives from wealth/royalty in the Ijebu dialect/culture. See: Okùbóyèjọ, Okùbádéjọ, Okùrónbí, Okùnúgà, Okùbánjọ, Okùsànyà, etc

name: Okùpè
extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.
gloss: [{'okù': ' - the god of wealth and resourcefulness'}]

name: Okùríbidó
meaning: The god of wealth has found a place to rest.
extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.
gloss: [{'Okù': ' - the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth and success'}]

name: Okùrónbí

extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.

name: Okùróunbí
meaning: The deity of enterprise has given birth to a (decent) child.
extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.

name: Okùsanmí
meaning: The god of industry benefits me.

name: Okùsànyà
meaning: The god of wealth paid for (my) suffering.
extended meaning: "Okù", the Ìjẹ̀bú god of wealth corresponds to "Ajé" the Ọ̀yó Yorùbá god of business and enterprise.
gloss: [{'okù': ' - the god of wealth and resourcefulness'}]

name: Okùsẹ̀hìndé
extended meaning: Okù in Ìjẹ̀bú has been compared to Ajé, the Ọ̀yọ́ god of business and enterprise.
gloss: [{'okù': ' - the god of business and resourcefulness (Ìjẹ̀bú)'}]

name: Okùyadé
meaning: Success and wealth has arrived in droves.
extended meaning: Okù in Ìjẹ̀bú has been compared to Ajé, the Ọ̀yọ́ god of business and entreprise.
gloss: [{'okù': ' - the Ìjẹ̀bú god of success and wealth'}]

name: Okùṣàmì
meaning: The god of business made a mark (on him/her).

name: Oláolúwatóní
meaning: The mercies of the Lord are enough.

name: Oládìtàn
meaning: (Our) wealth/success has become notable enough to be told as history.

name: Oláwándé
meaning: Wealth has pursued me to this place.

name: Oláyínká
extended meaning: Ọlá doesn't always mean wealth though. Read more: http://blog.yorubaname.com/2016/12/12/ola-isnt-always-wealth/

name: Olígbìndé
extended meaning: The ìgbìn refers to the drum used by the worshipers of Ọbàtálá.

name: Olochunde
meaning: Among the practitioners of Cuban òrìs̩à tradition, the name is said to mean "the coronation of Ochún/Oshún" (Ò̩s̩un in Yorùbá language). In the Yoruba language of west Africa, the name "O̩ló̩sundé" means "the priest of Ò̩s̩un has arrived. " Ò̩s̩un is a female yorùbá water deity.
extended meaning: Olochundé is used as a possible name for initiates of Ochún (Ò̩s̩un) within the cuban òrìs̩à tradition known as Santería or Lucumí.

name: Oloyaddé
meaning: In Cuban Orisa religion known as Lucumí religion or Santería (Regla de Ocha), the meaning they give is “the coronation (as in initiation of a novice into) the deity Oya. The original Yoruba language name that it is derived from is O̩ló̩yadé - the O̩ya priest has arrived (the owner of O̩ya has arrived)
gloss: [{'oní': ' - the owner of, the bearer of'}]

name: Olódó
gloss: [{'oní': ' - the owner of, the bearer of'}]

name: Ológun
gloss: [{'oní': ' - the owner of, the bearer of, the champion of'}]

name: Olókèdé
meaning: The owner of the hill arrived.

name: Olókètúyì
meaning: The people of the hill are honourable.

name: Olókodáná
meaning: The owner of the farm is the one that can make fire (with wood).

name: Olómidára
meaning: 1. The owner of good water. 2. The owner of water is good.
gloss: [{'olómi': ' - the owner of water, the bearer of water'}]

name: Olómidé
meaning: The owner/carrier /seller of water is here.

name: Olóògùnebi

name: Olóredé

name: Olóríire
meaning: Owner of a good head (destiny). The bringer of good luck.

name: Olóríjanbẹ́
meaning: The owner of the head did not allow it to be cut off.

name: Olóròdé
meaning: The owner of the Orò masquerade has arrived.

name: Olówófẹlá
meaning: The rich person rejoices in wealth.

name: Olówójọlá
meaning: 1. The rich person enjoys affluence. 2. The rich person enjoys benefits.

name: Olówólayémọ̀
meaning: The world only knows the rich.

name: Olówómojúọ̀rẹ́
meaning: (Even) the rich man knows the face of (his) friends.

name: Olówóníji
meaning: The rich man has a shade.

name: Olówóníyàn
meaning: A rich man/woman is not limited. Money/riches provide(s) options.

name: Olówóòfóyèkù
meaning: The rich do not belittle honour/chieftaincy.

name: Olówóòpẹjọ́
meaning: The rich isn't making any lawsuits.

name: Olówóparíìjà
meaning: The wealthy man intercedes in a dispute.

name: Olówóràrán
meaning: The rich bought clothes of velvet.

name: Olówóyẹyè
meaning: The rich man is deserving of honour.

name: Olówòfóyèkù
meaning: The rich does not lack more titles (as an addition to his wealth).

name: Olùmẹ̀gbọ́n
meaning: The Lord knows the eldest. [verification needed]

name: Olúbàjò
meaning: The head returns from a trip.
extended meaning: Either as a metaphor for the return of a dead person (father, grandfather) at the time of the child's birth, or a marker of a real life return of a parent when the child was born, the name talks about journeys and its relationship to the child's life.

name: Olúbádéwá
meaning: The prominent one came with royalty.

name: Olúbámbí
meaning: Heroism gave birth to (this) with me.

name: Olúbejidé
meaning: The lord came with the rain.

name: Olúbímpé
meaning: I was born into a family of leaders, and I was born perfect.

name: Olúbíni
meaning: 1. The prominent one gave birth to (me). 2. One given birth to by God/the prominent one.

name: Olúbísí
meaning: 1. God gave birth to. 2. Prominence gave birth to.

name: Olúbítán
meaning: The prominent one gave birth to whole.

name: Olúbùkúnọlámi
meaning: God has added to/increased my wealth.

name: Olúbùḿmọ̀
meaning: God gave me to know. God gave me knowledge.

name: Olúbùṣe
meaning: The lord (or, prominent one) has completed his work (on this child).

name: Olúbọlájí
gloss: [{'olú': ' - lord, chief, hero, olúwa, prominent one'}]

name: Olúbọ̀dé
meaning: A warrior has come; our lord has come.

name: Olúbọ̀sọlá
meaning: The master has returned into nobility/wealth.

name: Olúbọ́dún
meaning: The prominent one met a festival.
extended meaning:
This name is typically given to a child born during a festive event or season.

USER FEEDBACK

'Such a child is foreseen to be famous and courageous. There is a popular Yoruba saying in eulogizing person with such a name: "Olúbọ́dún dàgbà tán, apá ẹnìkan ò káa". Meaning, "The great child grows up to be undefeated."'

name: Olúbọ́dúnwá
meaning: The prominent one came with festivities.
extended meaning: This name is given to a child born during festivities, like Easter, Christmas, etc, or any traditional ceremony. See also: Olúbọ́dúnwá.

name: Olúbọ́rọ̀jí
meaning: The prominent one (child) woke up into wealth.

name: Olúdáìró
meaning: The lord kept this one (from dying).

This is a name given to an àbíkú child.
See also: Fádáìró.

name: Olúdára
meaning: HOMOGRAPH Olúdárà: The lord performs wonders. Olúdára: The lord is good.

name: Olúdárasími
meaning: The lord is good to me.

name: Olúdúró
meaning: The head awaits. The hero stands.
gloss: [{'olú': ' - lord, hero, chief, olúwa, prominent one'}]

name: Olúewu
meaning: 1. The king of risk. 2. The highest risk.

name: Olúfadéjì
meaning: The prominent one to whom royalty has been entrusted.

name: Olúfawo
gloss: [{'olú': ' - lord, chief, olúwa, hero, prominent one'}]

name: Olúfawoyè
meaning: The head survives with the oracle. [verification needed]
gloss: [{'olú': ' - head, chief, lord, prominent one, olúwa'}]

name: Olúfáyọ̀
gloss: [{'olú': ' - head, chief, prominent one, lord, olúwa'}]

name: Olúfọ́n
meaning: 1. The mushroom expands. 2. The name of the king of Ifọ́n
extended meaning:
Olúfọ́n means Ọbàtálá also known as Òrìṣà Olúfọ́n or Òrìṣànlá. It is translated simply as "King of the White Cloth"

It is also the title of King of Ifon, an ancient town founded by Oláòṣà Aládìkún who is reputed to be the first son of Ọbàtálá.

Oláòṣà Aládìkún was directed by Ifá to establish his town wherever he found Olu (mushrooms) spread on a tree populated by weaver birds literally translated as "ibi ti olu fon si" where mushrooms spread. Thus Olúfọ́n.

"Mushrooms spread" became synonymous with the King of Ifọ́n who is representative of Ọbàtálá (his progenitor) and the name is interchangeably used for Obàtálá because of his popularity and worship in Ifọ́n.

NOTE: The first Ifọ́n is in Ọ̀ṣun state while another one is in Ose local government of Ondo State. There is also Olúfọ́n of Ṣẹ̀pẹ̀tẹ̀rí and Olúfọ́n of Amọ́jẹ̀ in Oyo state.

(Note by Adémọ́la W. Tóyè)

name: Olú
meaning: 1. The head. 2. The prominent one. 3. The lord. 4. God (olúwa) 5. The hero/champion
extended meaning:
This is one of the most common roots of Yorùbá names, perhaps because it has also been modified in modern Christianity to refer to God. Initially, however, the name only referred to the most prominent version of something. e.g. Olú-Ọmọ (a child considered to be the most prominent, most relevant), Olú-Igbó (the lord of the forest), Olú-Ọ́dẹ (the head hunter), Olúòkun (the lord of the seas), Jagunmólú (He who fights to become the champion), etc.

In most modern interpretations, Olú is no longer just an almost nebulous root, it refers to Olúwa, which is Yorùbá's way of referring to the most prominent being, interpreted in modern times to mean Jesus Christ, or God Almighty.

Most old names bearing roots related to lesser deities (Ṣàngó, Ògún, Èṣù, Oṣó, etc) have been modernised to merely read Olú. e.g. Èṣùbíyí becomes Olúbíyí, Ògúnmodìmú becomes Olúmodìmu, Fájuyìgbé become Olújuyìgbé, etc.
