meaning: My child is enough to show off.
extended meaning: A child to be proud of. A child to be pampered. A child one can show off.

name: Ọmọnimẹ̀íwá
meaning: "I am looking for [a] child" OR "Getting a child is my aim."

name: Ọmọniyì
meaning: 1. The child is honour. (Ọmọniyì) 2. The child has honour/worth/value. (Ọmọ́níyì)

name: Ọmọniyiọlá
meaning: A child gives value or prestige to honor.

name: Ọmọrìnsọ́lá
meaning: The child walks serendipitously into wealth.

name: Ọmọtiwalọlá
meaning: This child of ours is wealth.

name: Ọmọtójífọláwẹ̀
meaning: The child who bathes in nobility from waking moments.

name: Ọmọtómilọ́lá
meaning: The child is enough for me as wealth.

name: Ọmọtórera
meaning: My child is enough to show off.
extended meaning: A child to be proud of. A child to be pampered. A child one can show off.

name: Ọmọ́bámimúra
meaning: The child dresses up with me. The child helps me prepare.

name: Ọmọ́boyèjẹ́
meaning: The child does not ruins the title.

name: Ọmọ́bùkọ́lá
meaning: The child adds to wealth. The child blesses (our) wealth.

name: Ọmọ́bùsọ́lámi
meaning: The child adds to my nobility/glory/wealth.

name: Ọmọ́bùwàjọ
meaning: The child has decent character. [verification required]

name: Ọmọ́bẹ́mìlẹ́numi
meaning: The child met me still breathing.
extended meaning: "A woman who was almost dead while in the labour room and later gave birth gave this name to the child" - User feedback

name: Ọmọ́bọlájí
meaning: The child woke up with wealth.

name: Ọmọ́bọ̀bọ́la
meaning: The child comes to meet nobility.

name: Ọmọ́bọ́jà
extended meaning: It's a name given to one born on the way to or from the market.

name: Ọmọ́bọ́ládé
meaning: This child came at the same time as wealth/honour/glory.

name: Ọmọ́bọ́lárìnwá
meaning: Born around the same time the family came into riches, success or wealth.

name: Ọmọ́dàmórí
meaning: The child mixes with the head

name: Ọmọ́dolúpọ̀
meaning: The child brings two families of prominence together.

name: Ọmọ́dùnbí
meaning: The child is sweet to birth (to have).

name: Ọmọ́dùnmọ́lá
meaning: A child is sweet with wealth.

name: Ọmọ́dásọ́lá
meaning: The child participates or joins in wealth.

name: Ọmọ́désọ́lá
meaning: This child has arrives into wealth or nobility.
extended meaning: This name is given to a child considered to have arrived into a wealthy family.

name: Ọmọ́dẹ̀hìndé
extended meaning:
This is a name given to a child in a family where children die recurrently ( àbíkú). It means the child that died the other time has arrived again.
It is a variant of the following names: Dẹ̀hìndé, Ọmọ́dẹ̀hìnbọ̀, Ọmọ́sẹ̀hìndé

name: Ọmọ́dọlápọ̀
meaning: The child has added more honour.

name: Ọmọ́fádé
meaning: HOMOGRAPH Ọmọ́fádé The child loves/wants the crown. ____ Ọmọ́fadé: 1. The child pulls the crown. 2. The child expands royalty.

name: Ọmọ́fisáyọ̀
meaning: A child is added to (my) joy.

name: Ọmọ́fóyè
meaning: 1. The child wants/loves honour. 2. The child wants a title.

name: Ọmọ́fẹlá
meaning: 1. The child is the epitome of the parents' fortune/success. 2. The child enlarges success. 3. The child luxuriates in success.

name: Ọmọ́fọlárìnwá
meaning: The child walks in with nobility.

name: Ọmọ́gbésímilọ́wọ́
meaning: Child is eternal in my hands.

name: Ọmọ́gbọ́láhàn
meaning: This child makes our wealth salient.

name: Ọmọ́gbọ́njúbọ́lá
meaning: The child grew up to meet success.

name: Ọmọ́goríọlá
meaning: The child is greater than wealth (riches).

name: Ọmọ́gùnlóyè
meaning: The child is long in honour/title.

name: Ọmọ́jíráyọ̀
meaning: The child wakes up to joy.

name: Ọmọ́jowó
meaning: The child is better than money.

name: Ọmọ́jowólọ
meaning: A child is more valuable than wealth.

name: Ọmọ́juwà
meaning: The child is our legacy. The child won't let our legacy go to waste.

name: Ọmọ́juwàgbé
meaning: The child won't let one's legacy go to waste.

name: Ọmọ́júohungbogbolọ
meaning: A child is the most important thing in the world.

name: Ọmọ́jọláẹbí
meaning: The child enjoys the grace/nobility/privilege of the family.

name: Ọmọ́kánjú
meaning: The child is in a hurry; the child is hasty

name: Ọmọ́káyọ̀dé
meaning: The child has brought joy in aundance.

name: Ọmọ́kúngà
meaning: There are plenty children in (our) throne room.

name: Ọmọ́kúnlé
meaning: The house (family) is filled with children.

name: Ọmọ́kẹ́hìndé
extended meaning: This is the name given to the second part of a twin.

name: Ọmọ́kẹ́yìndé
extended meaning: This is a name given to the second of twins.

name: Ọmọ́kọ́lápọ̀
meaning: The child brought success (from two families) together.

name: Ọmọ́làjà
extended meaning: This kind of child was given birth to during dispute between parents or parents' family; the birth of such child brings unity among the parents/ parents family.

name: Ọmọ́lèsì
meaning: The child has come as the response/answer.

name: Ọmọ́loyè
meaning: A child is a chieftancy title.

name: Ọmọ́lóluoyè
meaning: The chief fruit of chieftaincy is the child.

name: Ọmọ́mọwó
meaning: This child recognizes the value of money

name: Ọmọ́pẹ̀rọ̀sọ́lá
meaning: The child brought peace into wealth/nobility.

name: Ọmọ́pẹ́
meaning: The child took a while to arrive.
extended meaning: An abridgment of Ọmọ́pẹ́nínú (the child took a while in the womb).

name: Ọmọ́pẹ́nnú
meaning: The child took long in the womb.
extended meaning: This name is typically given with a longer gestation than nine months.

name: Ọmọ́pẹ́nínú
meaning: The child stayed too long in the womb.

name: Ọmọ́ráyéwá
meaning: This child came to a good life.

name: Ọmọ́rìnlóyè
meaning: The child walks to receive honour.

name: Ọmọ́rìnsọ́jọ́
meaning: The child walks into the (perfect) day. A perfectly-timed child.

name: Ọmọ́ríléwá
meaning: The child has found a home to come to.
extended meaning: A name for an adopted orphan, or a name simply given to appreciate such a beautiful child coming into this family.

name: Ọmọ́ríresọ́lá
meaning: The child sees goodness in wealth.

name: Ọmọ́ríyebá
extended meaning:
This is a name given to a child whose birth was surrounded by trials. The name implies a relief that the mother made it through the travails enough to meet the child.

It can also be for a child whose mother died shortly after he/she is born.

name: Ọmọ́rókè
meaning: The child has seen the mountain.

name: Ọmọ́róníkẹ
meaning: A child finds one who cares for her.

name: Ọmọ́sùnládé
meaning: The child rests on a crown.

name: Ọmọ́súnmibọ́lá
meaning: The child has moved me closer to success/wealth.

name: Ọmọ́sẹfun
meaning: 1. The child of the white cloth. 2. Ọbàtálá gave this child.

name: Ọmọ́tádé
meaning: The child is equal to the crown.

name: Ọmọ́táyọ̀mi
meaning: My child equates the joy I have.

name: Ọmọ́tiléwá
meaning: The child came from (a good) home.

name: Ọmọ́toríogun
meaning: The child, because of battle (came to the world).

name: Ọmọ́tókẹ́
meaning: It is only right to pamper a child.

name: Ọmọ́tómikẹ́
meaning: Having a child satisfies my desires. I am content with caring for a child.

name: Ọmọ́tómirera
meaning: This child is enough for me to show off.
extended meaning: A child to be proud of. A child to be pampered. A child one can show off.

name: Ọmọ́tóní
meaning: A child is a valuable asset.

name: Ọmọ́tóyè
meaning: The child is worth the chieftaincy.

name: Ọmọ́tóyọ̀sí
meaning: Having a child is worth celebrating.

name: Ọmọ́tùbora
meaning: The child is worthy of being covered with.

name: Ọmọ́tẹ́hìnṣe
meaning: A child that repairs what is left behind.

name: Ọmọ́tẹ́lẹ̀ọlá
meaning: The child prepares the ground for wealth.

name: Ọmọ́tẹ́ní
meaning: The child lays the mat (of wealth). An abridged form of Ọmọ́tẹ́níọlá.

name: Ọmọ́tẹ́níọlá
meaning: The child lays the mat of wealth. Shortened form: Ọmọ́tẹ́ní.

name: Ọmọ́tẹ́yìnṣe
meaning: The child takes good care of the home in one's absence.

name: Ọmọ́tọ́lání
meaning: The child is old/prominent/important enough to have wealth.

name: Ọmọ́wayé
meaning: The child arrives in the world.

name: Ọmọ́wáire
meaning: 1. The child came well 2. A child seeks favour.

name: Ọmọ́wáiyé
meaning: (An important) child came into the world.

name: Ọmọ́wálé
extended meaning: This was the Yorùbá name given to Malcolm X when he visited the University of Ìbàdàn in 1959: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malcolm_X

name: Ọmọ́wáléọlá
meaning: A child came to a home of wealth.

name: Ọmọ́wùmí
meaning: I am desirous of the child.

name: Ọmọ́wándé
meaning: The child sought and found me.

name: Ọmọ́wọnúọlá
meaning: The child enters into wealth. Wọnúọlá

name: Ọmọ́wọ́n
extended meaning: The name is given to children whose parents have been waiting to have children for a very long time.

name: Ọmọ́yájowó
meaning: The child is better than money.

name: Ọmọ́yẹlé
meaning: Children are a good fit for homes. This child is befitting of our home.

name: Ọmọ́yẹmí
meaning: The child befits me. The child bring honour to me.

name: Ọmọ́ṣaléwá
meaning: The child selected this house to come to.

name: Ọmọ́ṣẹ̀san
meaning: The child is a reward for some previous losses (of a child or other significant loss).

name: Ọmọ́dára
meaning: 1. The child is good (Ọmọ́dára). 2. The child creates wonders/The child is wonderful. (Ọmọ́dárà)

name: Ọmọ́jolá
meaning: The child is more than wealth.
extended meaning: The name is written either as Ọmọjọlá or Ọmọ́jọlà

name: Ọmọ́túndé
extended meaning: This is an abíkú name, given to a child believed to have returned after many arrivals and departures.

name: Ọnàbánjọ
meaning: Ornamental work (as a profession) is agreeable to me.

name: Ọnàfẹ̀sọ̀bí
meaning: Artistry gave birth to (this one) gently.

name: Ọnàmùtì
meaning: Artistic works (that I possess or have created) have taken (my) shame away (from me).

name: Ọnàsànyà
meaning: Ornamental work compensates (for a previous loss).

name: Ọnàyalé
meaning: (The descendant of) the ornamental worker detoured into (my) home.

name: Ọníbiyọ̀
meaning: The owner of the birth rejoices. [verification needed]

name: Ọpẹ́ìbí
meaning: 1. The benefit of (good) birth. 2. I'm proud of my heritage.

name: Ọpẹ́lámì
meaning: Gratefulness has a mark. Being thankful has a notable effect. [Verification needed]

name: Ọpẹ́lóyẹrú
meaning: Thanksgiving is deserving of the slave.

name: Ọpẹ́odù
meaning: Literal: The appreciation of the Ifá corpus. Figurative: We thank Ifá (or "If not for Ifá).

name: Ọpẹ́ọlá
gloss: [{'ọpẹ́': ' - thanks to, by the grace of'}]

name: Ọpẹ́yímiká
meaning: Thankfulness surrounds me. I'm surrounded by things that make me give thanks.

name: Ọpẹ́yínká
meaning: Things to be thankful for surrounds me. I'm surrounded by thankfulness/gratefulness.

name: Ọpẹ́yẹmí
meaning: 1. I should be grateful. 2. Thanksgiving suits me.

name: Ọrànmíyàn
meaning: The child has chosen to be controversial.
extended meaning: This is the name of Odùduwà's youngest grandson (some say a son of the god Ògún) who became the fourth or sixth Ọọ̀ni of Ìle-Ìfẹ̀, first Aláàfin of Ọ̀yọ́ and the first Ọba of Benin. He was deified as a god when he died.

name: Ọráfidíyà
meaning: The Ọrà used this to pay recompense.

name: Ọrẹolúwayímiká
meaning: The gift of God surrounds me.

name: Ọrẹ̀sànyà
extended meaning: The person who propitiates or worships the Ọrẹ̀ is called "Abọrẹ̀" the Priest.

name: Ọrẹ́méjì
extended meaning: This name is a story of love and friendship, stressing the friendliness between the parents beyond their romantic love.

name: Ọshìfalà
gloss: [{'ọṣìn': ' - The Ìjẹ̀bú god of wisdom, iron, and warfare.'}]

name: Ọshìn
meaning: The Ìjẹ̀bú god of wisdom, iron, and warfare.
extended meaning: This is a common root of many Ìjẹ̀bú names, like Oṣìnnọ́wọ̀, Ọṣìndípẹ̀, etc.

name: Ọsìbàjò
meaning: The (head of the) Ọṣìn divinity has returned from a journey.

name: Ọsìlàjà
meaning: The (head of the) Ọṣìn divinity has brought peace.

name: Ọsìmósù
meaning: The Ọṣìn has brought the camwood (to use on this child). Ọṣìnmósùn

name: Ọsìbódù
meaning: The (head of the) Ọṣìn divinity has met the oracle

name: Ọwá
meaning: Title of the king of the Ijesha.

name: Ọwásanóyè
meaning: The Ọwá benefited in royalty. [verification needed]
extended meaning: The Ọwá Obòkun is the titular head of the Ìjẹ̀ṣà people.

name: Ọyafúnkẹ́
meaning: The goddess Ọya gave me (this child) to cherish.

name: Ọyagòkè
meaning: The goddess Ọya (or her devotee) ascends (into greatness).

name: Ọyárínú
meaning: Ọya sees the insides (of a person).

name: Ọyásọ̀kò
gloss: [{'ọya': ' - the goddess of the river Niger'}]

name: Ọyátógun
meaning: The goddess Ọya is strong enough to go to war.

name: Ọyátólú
meaning: 1. Ọya is worth prominence. Ọya is worth being a god.

name: Ọyátóyè
meaning: The goddess Ọya is as prominent as honour.

name: Ọyátẹ́milọ́rùn
meaning: The goddess Ọya is sufficient for me.

name: Ọyátẹ́rù
gloss: [{'ọya': ' - the goddess of the River Niger'}]

name: Ọyáwọyè
meaning: The goddess Ọya has entered honour.

name: Ọ̀bíṣẹ̀san
extended meaning: Ẹ̀san can mean any of vengeance, reward, payback, recompense. Not always positive, but not always negative either.

name: Ọ̀dúndún
meaning: The appellation of a king of Akure.

name: Ọ̀gábìyí
meaning: The masquerade gave birth to this.

name: Ọ̀gúntìmẹ́yìn
gloss: [{'ògún': ' - Ògún, the Yorùbá god of metal.'}]

name: Ọ̀jáfọlákẹ́
meaning: The Ọ̀já cares for with nobility.
gloss: [{'ọ̀já': ' - the cloth used to carry children'}]

name: Ọ̀jájá
meaning: An appellation for the Ọọ̀ni of Ifẹ̀.
extended meaning: The full appellation is Ọ̀jájá fi ìdí ọ̀tẹ̀ já'lẹ̀.

name: Ọ̀jèdélé
extended meaning: This name is commonly borne by the custodian family of masquerades (Òjè).

name: Ọ̀jéwánwá
meaning: The masquerade came looking for me

name: Ọ̀jẹ̀bísí
meaning: The masquerade gave birth to more.

name: Ọ̀jẹ̀dòkun
meaning: The masquerade becomes huge as the ocean.

name: Ọ̀jẹ̀labí
meaning: We have given birth to a masquerade.

name: Ọ̀jẹ́bíyì
meaning: The masquerade gave birth to this.

name: Ọ̀jẹ́kúnlé
meaning: The family is full of Masquerade worshipers

name: Ọ̀kánjọ̀bí
extended meaning: Name given to the only male among many female siblings.

name: Ọ̀nàadé
meaning: The way of royalty. The path to the crown.

name: Ọ̀nàmíyólúwa
meaning: My path is clear to God.

name: Ọ̀nàọlámipọ̀
meaning: The ways of my wealth are many.

name: Ọ̀nàọlápọ̀
meaning: The ways of wealth are many.

name: Ọ̀nàọpẹ́mipọ̀
meaning: The ways in which I'm grateful are many.

name: Ọ̀nàọpẹ́mipọ̀fólúwa
meaning: I have many ways to give thanks to God.

name: Ọ̀nàọpẹ́pọ̀
meaning: The ways in which I'm grateful are many.

name: Ọ̀pábùnmi
extended meaning: This is a common name in egúngún or ẹ̀yọ̀ households.

name: Ọ̀pádìran
extended meaning: The Ọ̀pá is common among worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the god of fertility and farming.
gloss: [{'ọ̀pá': ' - the deity of fertility and farming'}]

name: Ọ̀pádòkun
meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity becomes as big as the ocean.

name: Ọ̀pádọ̀tun
meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity has been renewed.

name: Ọ̀pálúwà
gloss: [{'ọ̀pá': ' - Ọ̀pá, the deity of fertility, òrìṣà oko'}]

name: Ọ̀pánúbi
meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity has (a good) lineage.

name: Ọ̀pánúgà
meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity has a throne.

name: Ọ̀pátóyè
meaning: The staff is equal to the title.
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility and harvest. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Ọ̀pátọ́lá
meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity is worth success.

name: Ọ̀páwádé
meaning: The one the Ọ̀pá deity sought here.
extended meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity, also called Òrìṣà Oko, is the deity of agriculture and fertility.
gloss: [{'ọ̀pá': ' - the Ọ̀pá deity of farming and fertility'}]

name: Ọ̀páwándé
meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity sought me here.
extended meaning: The Ọ̀pá deity, also called Òrìṣà Oko, is the deity of agriculture and fertility.
gloss: [{'ọ̀pá': ' - the Ọ̀pa deity of farming and fertility'}]

name: Ọ̀pádèjì
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility and harvest. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Ọ̀pálẹ́yẹ
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility and harvest. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Ọ̀pádoyin
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility and harvest. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Ọ̀pákúnlé
meaning: The home is full of the totem of the Òrìṣà oko.
gloss: [{'ọ̀pá': ' - a totem pole of the deity of fertility'}]

name: Ọ̀páyẹmí
meaning: The staff/authority is befitting of me.
extended meaning: The ọ̀pá is a root common to names of worshippers of the Òrìṣà oko, the deity of fertility. Read more here: http://www.ifafoundation.org/orisha-oko

name: Ọ̀pẹ̀tọ́lá
meaning: The Ifá divination (board) is worth success.

name: Ọ̀rẹ́ṣadé
meaning: Friends are equal to the crown. Friendship makes royalty.

name: Ọ̀rọ̀mítọ́pẹ́
meaning: My story or my journey deserves God’s praise.

name: Ọ̀rọ̀olúwakìíyẹ̀
meaning: The word of the lord never fails.

name: Ọ̀sanyìnlókun
extended meaning: Ọ̀sanyìn (god) but in this context refers to people that worships Ọ̀sanyìn.

name: Ọ̀shuntókí
meaning: Ọ̀sun is worthy to be thanked.

name: Ọ̀suntókun
meaning: Ọ̀sun is as big as the ocean.

name: Ọ̀súngbémí
meaning: HOMOGRAPH 1. Ọ̀ṣun carries me (Ọ̀ṣungbémi) 2. Ọ̀ṣun supports me (Ọ̀ṣungbèmí)

name: Ọ̀táìbáyọ̀mí
meaning: Enemies would have mocked/ridiculed me (but God refused/prevailed).

name: Ọ̀túnba
meaning: The right-hand person of the king.

name: Ọ̀támáyọ̀mí
meaning: Enemy, do not rejoice! My enemy, do not mock me!

name: Ọ̀túnla
extended meaning:
Full: Ọ̀túnla-la-máa-dá-ifá: "We will consult the Ifa "the day after tomorrow."

This name is given to a child born after two other children named Òní (today) and Ọla (tomorrow)

name: Ọ̀tẹ́pọlá
meaning: Intrigues have killed the prominent member of this notable family.
extended meaning: This name is typically given after the death of a major patriarch in the family where Ọlá is typically given as a name.

name: Ọ̀tọkìtí
meaning: 1. One who jumps around in an elusive manner. 2. A person fond of somersaulting.

name: Ọ̀tọ̀lórìn
extended meaning: This is a name given to a child considered to be different either in appearance or in manner of birth.

name: Ọ̀ṣìnúgà
meaning: The king has a royal compound.

name: Ọ̀ṣíyẹmí
meaning: The Ọṣì(n) is worthy of me.
gloss: [{'ọṣìn': ' - the head, king, the deity Ọṣìn'}]

name: Ọ̀ṣínbàjò
meaning: The king has returned from a journey.
extended meaning:
"In his native Ijebu, one of the oldest and most distinct dialects of the Yoruba language, Ọsìn could also refer to a “child” and Ọsínbàjò (Osìn bọ̀ láti àjò) could then be interpreted to mean a child has returned from a journey." From https://www.thecable.ng/osibajo-osinbanjo-osinbajo-meet-nigerias-newest-politician-buharis-running-mate

Ọṣìn (also sometimes written as Ọsìn or Ọshìn) is common in many Ìjẹ̀bú names like Ọsìnọ́wọ̀ or Ọ̀shítẹ̀lú, etc, referring to the Ọṣìn divinity.
gloss: [{'ọṣìn': " - king (as used in Ẹrú Ọṣìn: the King's slave)"}]

name: Ọ̀ṣunfúnkẹ́
meaning: Ọ̀ṣun gave me to be cherished.

name: Ọ̀ṣuntúnmiṣe
meaning: Ọ̀ṣun edified me. i.e. Ọ̀ṣun brought me to a state of beauty. Ọ̀ṣun repaired me.

name: Ọ̀ṣúndoyin
extended meaning: User feedback: "This name was revealed by Ọ̀rúnmìlà for our daughter during her naming ceremony and in association with Odù Ọ̀bàrà-Rẹtẹ̀."

name: Ọ̀ṣúndọjà
meaning: The goddess Ọ̀ṣun has become prosperous (like a marketplace).
extended meaning:
The deeper meaning is the fact that when you go to a market, there’s plenty, surplus, value, money, and every good and new thing. The combination of all these things with the power and fame of Ọ̀ṣun gives the name a perfect fit and unique meaning.

See: Adédọjà, Ògúndọjà, Ọládọjà, etc.

name: Ọ̀ṣúnfowórà
meaning: What the goddess Ọ̀ṣun bought with money.

name: Ọ̀ṣúnkẹ́mi
meaning: The goddess Ọ̀ṣun cares for me.

name: Ọ̀ṣúnlẹ́yẹ
extended meaning: Ọ̀ṣun isi associated with life such as in fertility and healing; she is also associated with love, sensuality, and beauty.

name: Ọ̀ṣúntúbọ̀
extended meaning: The full name would be Ọ̀ṣuntúbọ̀ṣún. See also: Ọlátúbọ̀sún.
gloss: [{'ọ̀ṣun': ' - Yorùbá river goddess associated with life such as in fertility and healing; she is also associated with love, sensuality, and beauty'}]

name: Ọ̀ṣúnyọyin
meaning: Ọṣun brings the honey or Osun drizzles honey etc

name: Ọ̀ṣúnṣàmì
meaning: Osun makes a mark or gives a sign (with/on this child).

name: Ọ̀ṣúndárà
meaning: Ọ̀ṣúndárà: Ọ̀sun has created wonder. Ọ̀ṣundára: Ọ̀ṣun is good.

name: Ọ̀ṣọ́sàmì
meaning: Artistry made a mark (on this child).

name: Ọ̀ṣọ́fisan
extended meaning: 'If you explain "Ọ̀ṣọ́" as "The god/goddess of beauty, or adornment, or enrichment, etc," then it's easy to figure out the rest. It means that this god/dess is paying back, or rewarding, with this.' - Fẹ́mi Ọ̀ṣọ́fisan (playwright)

name: Ọṣidẹ̀rọ̀
extended meaning: [If you know the meaning of this name, please send it to us using the "improve this entry" button.]

name: Ọṣifala
gloss: [{'Ọṣìn': ' - The Ìjẹ̀bú god of wisdom, iron, and warfare.'}]

name: Ọṣìfọdúnrìn
meaning: The leader chose a time of festivities to arrive.

name: Ọṣìkọ̀yà
gloss:
It is most likely a name given to a child believed to have followed a long line of àbikú children who die as soon as they're born.

'Yeku is an imperative to "stop dying." It is probably a wrong spelling my ancestors settled for but it is different from "Ọ̀yẹ̀kú" (of the Ifa, for example). It is NOT a short form.' - James Yékú

name: Ugbódín
meaning: The bush/forest has grown so close together, we can't get in (to bury a dead child).

name: Wáléadé
meaning: Come to the home of royalty.

name: Wálé
extended meaning: This is a common short form of Ọláwálé, Adéwálé, Ọmọ́wálé, etc

name: Yanjú
extended meaning: This is a common short form of Adéyanjú or Olúyanjú, etc.
